description.189:
Meet other developers and ops engineers using Docker. Docker is an open platform for developers and sysadmins to build, ship, and run distributed applications. Consisting of Docker Engine, a portable, lightweight runtime and packaging tool, and Docker Hub, a cloud service for sharing applications and automating workflows, Docker enables apps to be quickly assembled from components and eliminates the friction between development, QA, and production environments. As a result, IT can ship faster and run the same app, unchanged, on laptops, data center VMs, and any cloud.

Learn more about Docker at http://www.docker.com
description.190:
PyLadies Vancouver is a Python programming group for women in the Vancouver area.

Persons with any gender identity are welcome, and should respect that PyLadies Vancouver must be a place where women's voices are centred.

We expect everyone attending our meetups to abide by our Code of Conduct.

PyLadies is an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings.
description.191:
CodeUp Manchester is a mentoring program for adults who would like to learn how to code for free. Once a month we provide a workspace for people with no programming skills to come and learn the basics, with mentors available to answer your questions and help you on your way. Our sessions will also be suitable for people with basic skills who need support to develop them, and even for people with intermediate or advanced skills who just want to come along to a space where everyone is immersed in code!

We are currently running sessions on the 4th Wednesday of the month at Building Blocks Manchester near Piccadilly Gardens.. 

If you have any suggestions on what you would like to see in these sessions, or if you would like to join us as a mentor, please contact the organisers!
description.192: This is a group for anyone who is interested in Python or Python based projects looking to meetup with fellow Pythonistas.
description.193:
We will be exploring and discussing: "The Rise of the Unikernel"
One of the key focuses will be comparing Unikernels to Containers.
description.194:
New Haven IO is an aggregator for all hacker-related stuff going on in New Haven, CT. Lots of us use Ruby, and lots of us use JavaScript, but there's mobile too, and Python, and Processing.

We’re starting the next big phase for the New Haven tech scene, and could use your help. If you’re interested in programming, the intertubes, and whatnot, please get in touch. We started a Google Group and are on Twitter at @newhavenio.

If you want to help us build the website, please start contributing to our repo on GitHub.
description.195:
The Cleveland Game Developers (CGD) is an open group of artists, developers, designers and musicians. We welcome everyone of any skill level interested in creating games or discussing them. We offer our members a regular monthly meeting as well as presentations, workshops and game jam events.

We also abide by a Social Code and Anti-Harassment Policy that promotes group collaboration, respect and inclusion.

Social Code: http://bit.ly/10GctIf

Anti-Harassment Policy: http://bit.ly/10Gdm3E
description.196:
On the last Friday of the month, we get together for an all-night hacking session.

Stay as long or as short as you'd like.

This group is for anyone who wants to catch up on that nagging side project at a late night, caffeinated coding session with like-minded individuals.

All skill levels and languages are welcome! Designers and entrepreneurs welcome too, come get some work done!
description.197: Open to all those interested in Apache Cassandra, Big Data, Hadoop, Hive, Hector, NoSQL, Solr, and high scalability. Let's get together and share what we know.
description.198: Python is a powerful, very approachable programming language.  Come to our group and participate in discussions and educational presentations about it.  We welcome those new to Python as well as those who have using it for years.  We have two social meetings and two hands-on technical meetings each month.  We cover many problem domains from serving web pages and database programming, to programs for systems administration and game programming.
description.199:
We are a group of Python web developers from Berlin who use Django–the Python Web Framework.

We also use a mailing list to stay in contact. Feel free to subscribe!

https://groups.google.com/group/django-berl... (django-berlin@googlegroups.com)

Usually we speak English, no knowledge of the German language is required.

Our ground rules are documented in the Berlin Code of Conduct: http://rubyberlin.github.io/code-of-conduct...
description.200:
Monthly meetup for those using python, learning python of just py-curious. Python is one of more popular programming languages in the word and rising further, being used in fields such as web, science, big data, dev-ops and digital entertainment. We to have talks from beginners to advanceก and provide a friendly atmosphere to meet and network with your fellow pythonistas.
Meetup รายเดือนสำหรับผู้ที่ใช้ภาษา Python หรือผู้ที่อยากเรียนรู้ หรือแม้แต่ผู้ที่แค่อยากรู้ว่า Python คืออะไร Python เป็นหนึ่งในภาษาเขียนโปรแกรมที่ได้รับความนิยมมากขึ้นเรื่อยๆ ซึ่งถูกนำมาใช้ในด้านของการพัฒนา website, งานด้านวิทยาศาสตร์, ข้อมูลขนาดใหญ่, dev-ops และความบันเทิงระบบดิจิตอล เราจะมีการพูดคุยแนะนำจากระดับ beginners ถึงระดับ advance ในบรรยากาศที่เป็นกันเองเพื่อคุณจะได้ทำความรู้จัก และ network กับ Pythonistas เช่นคุณ

Also join the facebook group
description.201:
We are a social/professional group for women who are Python programmers at every experience level, in the Portland, OR area. Developers and aspiring developers, please! Join us on IRC - #pyladiespdx or find us on Twitter @PyLadies_pdx. We have guides and other set-up materials on Github as well.


We typically meet every other Tuesday and most Saturdays, and we host three types of meetings:

* All women welcome

* Women and their invited guests

* All are welcome

Please check the meeting description to determine which type of meeting we're having.

All Pyladies meetups, events, and forums (including our meetup page, our mailing lists, and other online channels) are governed by the Pyladies Code of Conduct.
description.202:
106 Miles is a network of startup founders, engineers, and friends.


Our mission is to educate and empower entrepreneurial engineers.

Our values are Reputation, Innovation, Solidarity, and Education.

This is our Silicon Valley group; see also our Southern California group.


Please join us if you're a founder or engineer (or friend!) and...

* You have worked at a startup,

* You want to work at a startup,

* You have started a company, and/or

* You want to start a company.

We meet a few times a month (second Wednesday of each month in Palo Alto, 6-9pm, and the fourth Wednesday of each month in San Francisco, 6-9pm; and now Southern California too) to...

* Socialize and learn from each other.

* Exchange ideas and information. Informally. Usually in a bar.

* Meet people at new startups.

* Meet people who want to work at startups.


106 Miles is symbolic of the journey entrepreneurs that take.

It's from The Blues Brothers:

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gvKs2VLmVnY

Elwood: "It's 106 miles to Chicago, we got a full tank of gas, half a pack of cigarettes, it's dark, and we're wearing sunglasses."

Jake: "Hit it."


Please follow us on Twitter, like us on Facebook, and join us in person...
description.203:
Welcome to the official RethinkDB SF meetup group -- RethinkDB is an open-source, distributed database, built to store JSON documents at scale.

Join us the 2nd Thursday of every month in San Francisco!
description.204: Due to the growing python user community around Zurich, we decided to establish an opportunity for anyone who is interested in python to exchange, network and learn.
description.205: A monthly meetup of Python developers from Zagreb and region.
description.206: We want to promote the use of the Python programming language in the Middle Tennessee. Our primary purpose is to share knowlege and to nurture a community of Python professionals and enthusiasts. Each meeting is open to the public and aims to provide useful content for both novices and professionals. We abide by the PyCon Code of Conduct at all functions!
description.207:
Who are we?

We're an eclectic group formed by students, artists, engineers, developers, tinkerers, and hobbyists with a wide range of skills and interests who share a common curiosity about Do-It-Yourself projects involving Hardware Electronics.

We are a community open to everyone: from those who just want to get a general sense of the basics of electronics and programming, to those with the technical savvy to pursue projects on their own.

What do we do?

The list of activities is open ended, and we continuously seek to benefit our members in the best way we can; as such, we keep trying to figure out the best set of activities to achieve this goal.  Since April 2014 our meetups have involved:

- Informal monthly meetings for working on projects (individually or as group), show and tells, troubleshooting, and informal instruction of various aspects of Hardware Electronics.

- Hands-on workshops for learning or enhancing a specific skill.  We charge for the materials (if any) needed for the workshop.

- Classes properly structured to cover a topic in depth such as Intro to E-Textiles, Hardware Electronics, and the Internet of Things.  Fees associated with the classes cover the materials and the instructor's time.

Interested in sponsoring an event?

If you are organizing an event related to what we do, and are interested in having our members participate we can schedule it as a Sponsored Event.  For more details please contact us at team@makerden.io.

Facebook: http://facebook.com/makerdenio

Twitter: http://twitter.com/makerden

Github: http://github.com/makerdenio
description.208: The Quant Club is for anyone interested in quantitative finance and machine learning. We plan regular face-to-face meetings in LA where we share ideas and thoughts about quantitative finance. The Quant Club is for people interested in learning more about algorithmic trading. We are going to invite speakers to present their research. A special interest of the Quant Club is the application of machine learning tools for building quantitative trading systems. We are looking forward to meeting with you to jointly build trading systems using machine learning and other techniques.
description.209: This group is a place for developers to learn more about MongoDB, an open source, document-oriented, nosql database. If you are facing challenges with MySQL or Postgres or Oracle and want to explore a more flexible, scalable alternative, please join us at one of our monthly sessions.
description.210: Este grupo es para todos los interesados en el lenguaje de programación Python, que quieran aprender, enseñar, compartir sus experiencias, y sobre todo pasarla bien! Este Meetup es promovido y organizado por Python Argentina: http://python.org.ar/ Si te interesa participar en la organización podés suscribirte a nuestra lista: http://python.org.ar/lista/
description.211: The Pittsburgh Python User Group is a group that meets monthly to discuss Python development. We benefit from a variety of python developers in web application development, systems administration, and scientific programming. We hold occasional special events and hack nights. All of our meetings are open to the public, and anyone is welcome.
description.212: We believe a core skill of engineers is learning, teaching, and conveying concepts succinctly. The goal of this meetup is to improve both our teaching and learning skills while discovering some technical tricks we didn't know about before. Each meetup will host a series of lightning talks focused on specific technical topic, for example: the command line, automated testing, code reviews, text editors, front-end development, api development, algorithms, git.
description.213:
This group is for those who use the Python computer language or who want to learn more about the language. Python is a great language for rapid development and has some great web frameworks that make getting a functional web application up and running quite easily.

Please also join the Central Ohio Python Users Group mailing list at: http://mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/centraloh
description.214: The Waterloo region Python group. We are focused on helping people learn and do awesome things with Python.
description.215:
Formally the Django Houston Meetup, we have converted to the Python Web Development Meetup to expand our topics. We will cover high to low level topics over Python Web Development. It is assumed that you have some basic knowledge in python.

Here are some resources to wet your appetite:

    Django

    Django Tutorial

    Python

    Python Tutorial

    Flask

See you at the meetup!
description.216:
Whether you are an expert Python developer or just learning how to program, this is a group for those of us that want to meet with like minded people who are into programming with the Python language and don't have the time or inclination to be driving out to LA, Orange county, or San Diego just to meet for a few hours.

This is a group to share what you are doing with Python, to learn about topics related to the language, and to get help from others if you are stuck on something. Python is a very versatile programming language and it is used for a variety of applications and in a multitude of niche markets. From web development using Django, Flask, Pyramid, or CherryPy, to scripting other programs like Maya, Blender, FreeCAD or LibreOffice. From creating stand alone desktop applications for GIS applications or 3D printing, to rapidly developed utility applications for automated backup programs and web page scraping.

It can be quite surprising and inspirational when you find out what others have been doing with the Python language, and sharing and learning about Python in a loosely structured environment is what this group is about.  So if you're into Python and are milling about in the IE (Temecula, Riverside, Redlands, Moreno Valley, San Bernardino, Ontario, Upland, Corona, Palm Springs, etc.), come and join us!  We are currently meeting in Riverside on the third Tuesday of every month.
description.217:
This is a users group for Django (and Python) set up by people in the Bristol and Bath area of the UK in 2008. If you're a Django / Python user not in Bristol or Bath, don't let that stop you from joining! 

To help advertise it to the wider local Python community we have added a meetup site to the traditional organisation tool of the DBBUG Google Group that has been going for the last 7 years at https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/dbug

For a more detailed introduction to Python and the DBBUG group see the following presentation from the 2013 Bristol MegaMeet - a conference that brought together all the Bristol tech meetup groups

http://bit.ly/1PvU4KS
description.218: bi-monthly meetups around town with focus on mostly Google Technologies (what isn't nowadays?) with deep forays into programming language design, cloud services devops and CI, how to create cool games and a fair dose of web technologies as well. Sometimes just whimsical, but in a good way :)
description.219:
The developer who founds his own start-up has to learn rapidly how to act as the CEO. Successful start-uppers share their knowledge and discuss their business paths.

Lately, an accelerating number of tech start-ups develop to being successful businesses. The core role of the developer has changed a lot requiring new skills in organizing people and resources.

The Meet-Up will take place during the 4th Developers Day Event organized by kariera.gr.
description.220: We are a group of Systems Engineers and DevOps folks who want to Ansible all the things. Want to learn more about Ansible? Come join us. Already know Ansible well? Come share your knowledge.
description.221:
The Python language is a rarity in the software industry: accessible to almost everyone, versatile across application domains and generally a joy to work with. While enjoying Python alone is beneficial, PyRVA believes that Python is best enjoyed in the company of others. We are busy organizing talks, hackathons, workshops and more to help build up the Python community here in Richmond. Ideas are welcome.

Follow us on Twitter and GitHub.
description.222: Inspired by the role technology plays in daily life, we organize devs, designers, artists, and any interested in pushing the envelope from the grassroots by meetings, office hours, events, and workshops. All levels are welcome.
description.223:
Meet and drink beer with other local Software Developers. Discuss various programming languages and techniques, software architecture, cross-platform development, iPhone development, etc. We're an informal, social group designed to get most of us out of the office/home.

Our members cover a huge cross-section of the programming industry, from web to embedded, desktop to iPhone, from Java to C++ to Haskell.

If you program, either professionally or as a hobby, you'll probably get something from our group.
description.224: Meet other local programmers, learn something and have some fun. Anyone who writes a line of code is invited. This group's goal is to bring together the cross language, cross platform and cross industry developers that live on PEI.
description.225: This is a group for those interested in learning how to develop and operate MongoDB at scale. Come to one of our monthly meetups to learn about MongoDB, network with other technologists like you and meet MongoDB engineers.
description.226:
A group for anyone interested in Python, Django, cloud computing, deployment, provisioning, virtualization and related technologies. We'll meet up every two months at venues in and around Amsterdam, including the HQ of hostingcompany Byte. All skill levels are welcome!

Interested in doing a (lightning) talk or any other questions or suggestions? Get in touch with us!
description.227: This is a group for anyone interested in becoming a better DevOps engineer. We discuss things about deployment issues, delivery, integration, automation, security, powershell and bash scripts we use, to make our and your life easier and other tools to increase our cooperation between software developers and other IT professionals.
description.228:
Postlight is an agency that builds big, beautiful tech things.

We're a team that turns huge ideas into web and mobile products.  Whatever that takes, we do it. Platform architecture, front-end development, Android and iOS--we do it all.

But we won't do it alone. We are building a network of like-minded individuals. We're going to throw as many parties as we can, host as many speakers as we can, and share whatever we learn with the community as a whole.

That's where you come in! We hope to build a community, and the first part of building that community is getting everyone in the same room drinking and talking. Let's start there on October 27th.
description.229:
The East Troy Computer Club is a community-driven group of all-age, all-skill level tinkerers interested in playing with technology. We meet every other week (or so) over a variety of topics at a cafe on the historic square of East Troy, WI.

This club is about a year old now. Smaller meetups tend to take on a roudntable discussion format while larger turnouts/topics are more formal in presentation. Feel free to jump in on the conversation, show & tell your latest project or challenge.

Each meetup will have a theme and loose agenda to guide the group. Some will be geared towards kids, or helping grandparents out with getting their email to work. Others, and likely most consistently, we'll be a group of adults talking mostly about internet and hardware technologies. A little on the advanced side, but what better group of talented folks to serve as a backbone to a club such as this!

Things we're open to meeting over:

• Arts & Craft projects utilizing technology. 
• Robotics. Ardiuno, Raspberry Pi, Tessel hardware projects. 
• Web development, design, scaling and performance. 
• Hands-on workshops. Such as 'intro to electronics' for children. 
• Summer 'bootup camps'—Computer summer camp for kids. 
• Programming, Unit tests, Development tools and tips. 
• GNU/Linux, UNIX and general System Administration. 
• Productivity, Workflow and staying focus. 
• Collecting/Mining local (meta) data.
• Practicing your presentation skills with us. 
• Sprints (work on projects together, right then and there). 
• Tutorials / HOWTO's - An instructor walks the group through a particular topic. 
• Helping Seniors stay connected. 
• Sharing tips, tricks and software.

As we grow, certain interests or projects may branch out of this club, such as working with the Public Library and other facilities. We also have a GitHub organization; http://github.com/etcc/

We're a patient body of tinkerers invested in local community and set out to foster discovery and education of technology.

You don't have to be from East Troy to participate. Come on over!
description.230: Calling all Pythonistas! Other people using python in the OKC metro DO EXIST! Let's all meet each other and learn!
description.231:
Apache Spark collaborative coding session. 

Each Dojo, is an opportunity to work in groups, on specific challenges. 

The goal is to learn, while connecting with fellow members of the London Spark coding community. 

The meet up, is open to all, regardless of your Spark skills, all you need is a laptop.
description.232: Grupo de usuarios Python Valencia: somos un grupo de gente interesados en Python o cualquier tecnología que lo envuelve. Solemos hacer quedadas mensuales para compartir experiencias y además tomar algo ;)
description.233:
Visit us at http://www.novapython.org/

We talk about building applications using Python. Anything from startup prototypes to advanced data analysis with Numpy and Scipy. Python is a great choice due to the vast support community and ease of development.

The Northern Virginia Python Users Group gets together on the third Thursday of the month at the Science Logic location just off the Dulles Toll Road. We talk about beginning topics as well as more advanced applications of the language.
description.234:
Hack Salem is a monthly meetup for anybody in the Salem area that's interested in programming, hardware hacking, Making, or other sorts of generally nerdy and geeky topics.

We meet on the second Wednesday of every month in a mid-town Salem location. We generally have one or two technical presentations and general geeky chatter.
description.235:
A monthly meetup of python programmers and people interested in programming. 

All levels of experience are welcome - from dipping your feet in the waters of programming, to pros.

This meetup echoes the content on http://www.pythonedinburgh.org/ - please sign up at https://mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/edinburgh for official announcements.
description.236: This group is for people interested in cloud computing and also for those, who want to start new adventure with cloud.
description.237: Bunch of technology enthusiasts who have been organizing various User Group Meetups for Linux, JavaScript and Python. We decided to collate our efforts and start Mumbai Technology Meetup. We have been having regular offline meetups since the past 1 year for all the above and now look forward to making it more exciting by having a mixed crowd sharing and creating new learning experiences.
description.238: Baltimore city (and Baltimore-area) Pythonistas! I live in the city, and I wanted a meetup for Python programmers in the city. (But not exclusively! Of course all BW-area Pythonistas are welcome.)
description.239: Meet others in Philly interested in PostgreSQL: The World's Most Advanced Open Source Database. Discuss this open source database and share the tips and tricks you've learned using it.
description.240:
This is a meetup for {Cmd, R, Py, Matlab}Stan users. We'll have talks, Q&A sessions, and workshops.



Stan (http://mc-stan.org) is a probabilistic programming language implementing full Bayesian statistical inference with

• MCMC sampling (NUTS, HMC)

and penalized maximum liklelihood estimation with

•  Optimization (L-BFGS)

Stan is coded in C++ and runs on all major platforms (Linux, Mac, Windows).

Stan is freedom-respecting, open-source software (new BSD core, GPLv3 interfaces).
description.241:
OpenShift is Red Hat's public cloud application development and hosting platform that automates the provisioning, management and scaling of applications so that you can focus on writing the code for your business, startup, or next big idea.

This meetup will be a way for local cloud enthuisists to get together, share ideas, learn, and best of all hack!
description.242: We have regular meetings consisting of several short presentations followed by a longer main presentation. Everyone if free to attend and we often have snacks and drinks to foster a climate where discussions are welcome and appreciated. No particular skill level is required to enjoy the meetings since there is often a presentation for everyone, from new comers to experts. Beside the regular meetings, we often organize code sprints and informal gatherings. In 2014 and 2015 Montréal-Python will host the famous North American PyCon Conference.
description.243:
This is a group for anyone interested in in the Python computer language, from absolute beginners to experts. We're enthusiastic, polite and beginner-friendly. The group exists to share ideas and expertise, facilitate discussion and share the fun of Python in southern Colorado.
We generally have a project night on the second Tuesday of the month and presentations on the fourth Tueday.
description.244: This group is for all ages of developers in the Wasatch Front. We will do talks, code hacking, kata challenges, just to name a few. This group will be ever evolving to the needs of our development community. If you are a seasoned vet or a complete n00b, we want to see you at the LDUG Meetup.  Bring along anyone and plan to have loads of fun!
description.245:
We are a group of app developers based in Long Beach. We want to get together and talk about products that we've shipped. Each meetup will feature a show and tell, including code examples. We will have developers on-hand to talk about process and architectural direction. Beginners welcome!

Our website
description.246:
The Portland Data Science group focuses learning and implementing techniques in data mining and visualization. The group will focus on Python, R, and D3.javascript, but this is essentially a language agnostic group and all technologies are welcomed! This is an open space with a focus on beginners.

There are more resources located here:

http://www.meetup.com/Portland-Data-Science-Group/about/
description.247: Code Fellows offers full-time and part-time programs to train software developers at every experience level. We strongly believe in the power of community and want to contribute in any way we can. Whether you're just starting out or have been a coding for years, come join us!
description.248:
English: GDG Open Lima is a local chapter of the Google Developer Groups community in Lima. We're developers who like sharing awesome ideas. If you want to meet with other developers for coding, making and sharing interesting stuff, join us now!

Español: GDG Open Lima es una capítulo local del Google Developer Groups. Somos desarrolladores que gustamos de compartir grandes ideas. Si deseas reunirte con otros desarrolladores para codear o hacer y compartir cosas interesantes, únetenos ahora!

Disclaimer:
English: GDG Open Lima is an independent group; our activities and the opinions expressed on this site should in no way be linked to Google, the corporation. Español: GDG Open Lima es un grupo independiente; nuestras actividades y las opiniones expresadas en este sitio no deberán ser vinculadas a Google, la corporación.
description.249: Un rendez-vous (régulier ?) pour la communauté développeurs Python et ceux qui s'intéressent à cet éco-système. Ce peut être un lieu de présentation de projets et d'échanges conviviaux.
description.250: Utilisateurs et fans du framework web Django. Le framework pour les perfectionnistes qui ont des deadlines. Et qui aiment les poneys :)
description.251: Partager autour du language python, de ses pratiques, de sa technique et de son ecosysteme
description.252:
An upcoming regular event for people interested in Big Data, whether you are professionals in the field, enthusiasts, or students looking to build your career in that direction. We'll host interesting talks from industry experts, a focus on both business and technical aspects of big data, and plenty of time for networking!

Big Data, Vienna is hosted and managed by Dataconomy Media GmbH. Please get in touch with events@dataconomy.com if you are interested in participating.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v-ryAXdftUQ
description.253: This is a group for anyone who's interested in learning, developing, chatting about, and networking around Python in China's Northern Capital. The idea is to get together for anything from simple meet-and-greets to presentations, hackathons, and other events. To begin with we'll meet once per month probably in/around the Sanlitun area. I know there are a lot of tech people in and around Zhongguancun so if there is enough interest/participation we can consider either moving to a more central location or holding two separate events. Feedback in this area is welcome. The group is open to both local Chinese and foreign expats. The primary working/spoken language will be English but please don't let that hold you back! Looking forward to meeting my fellow Beijing pythonistas.
description.254: Meet some other folks programming on the Sunshine Coast. All skill levels welcome. The idea is to meet socially and possibly if we people interested in presenting get some updates and chat about new tech.
description.255:
Meetup for Barcelona Tech professionals interested in changing job and share information about which of the many startups and tech companies in the city are worth working for.

We talk about salaries, work mates, programming practices used, office atmosphere, (good/bad) bosses ...

We also like to visit startups and meet their CTOs.

This meetup is for technical people only: Developers, CTOs, system administrators, UI/UX devs, testers - you're all welcome. 


Are you a tech company and want to host this meetup as a way to let engineers know you? Let's get in touch at info@jobsbcn.com
description.256: We are a group of Systems Engineers and DevOps folks who want to Ansible all the things. Want to learn more about Ansible? Come join us. Already know Ansible well? Come share your knowledge.
description.257: Wow ... najbardziej wyluzowana Śląsku grupa miłośników programowania. Zapraszamy na cykliczne spotkania, na których będziemy rozmawiać o programowaniu, generalnie - dobre praktyki, nowinki technologiczne, technologie i narzędzia godne uwagi, rozwiązania popularnych problemów programistycznych, testowanie, bezpieczeństwo i wiele innych ciekawych tematów. Uszanowanko!
description.258:
A group for everyone interested in Python, Python-related technologies and programming in general.

Files, code snippets and presentations can be found in our GitHub repository:

https://github.com/skorokithakis/pythess-files
description.259:
We are the Sydney branch of an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings. PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!

PyLadies Sydney is welcoming to and respectful of trans women. We encourage all women to come out to our meetups.
description.260:
Bucks County Women in Tech exists to support women working in tech by providing venues to network, mentor and learn from others living or working in the Bucks County area.

Our vision is to create a network of empowered women who feel supported in their pursuit of successful careers in technology. We strive to provide events that facilitate learning about technology as well as from each others' experiences.

Note: While we focus our mission and messaging to women, we're women inclusive, not women-only.
description.261:
Google Developer Group New Hampshire meets every month in Manchester, NH. We are a community of developers and enthusiasts that are interested in harnessing the power of Google. Our community will bring together developers from all walks of life and facilitates an open, collaborative, engaging atmosphere for learning, discussion, and creation.

We will explore Google API's and products in a format that meets the demands of our members.

Our nickname is our Hashtag: #GDGNH

Disclaimer: GDG New Hampshire is an independent group; our activities and the opinions expressed here should in no way be linked to Google, the corporation.
description.262:
User Group for Python developers, enthusiast and hackers of the Kansas City Metro Area and surroundings.

http://pythonkc.com

description.263: This is the meetup group of the Python Users Group in Athens, Greece.
description.264:
Follow us!

Facebook: WWCodeAccra

Twitter: @WWCodeAccra #wwcode

Mission:

Women Who Code is a global nonprofit organization dedicated to inspiring women to excel in technology careers by creating a global, connected community of women in technology. The organization tripled in 2013 and has grown to be one of the largest communities of women engineers in the world.

Empowerment:

Women Who code is a professional community for women in tech. We provide an avenue for women to pursue a career in technology, help them gain new skills and hone existing skills for professional advancement, and foster environments where networking and mentorship are valued.

Key Initiatives:

Free technical study groups

Events featuring influential tech industry experts and investors

Hack events

Career and leadership development

Current and aspiring coders are welcome. 

Bring your laptop and a friend! 

Support Women Who Code:

Donating to Women Who Code, Inc. (#46-4218859) directly impacts our ability to efficiently run this growing organization, helps us produce new programs that will increase our reach, and enables us to expand into new cities around the world ensuring that women and girls everywhere have the opportunity to pursue a career in technology.

Code of Conduct for Events:

Women Who Code (WWCode) is dedicated to providing an empowering experience for everyone who participates in or supports our community, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, ability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or socioeconomic status. Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. Our Code of Conduct applies to all events run by Women Who Code, Inc. If you would like to report an incident or contact our leadership team, please submit an incident report form.

WomenWhoCode.com

Twitter | Facebook
description.265: This is the group for Python Developers of Nepal. We plan to meetup regularly and would be announcing all meetups via this group.

description.268:
A casual, welcoming group for open source software developers, users, and other interested folks to learn and share. All experience levels welcome!

  • Find us on Twitter at @opensourcelala
description.269:
The Ybor Tech Association exists to grow, encourage and support the tech community in Ybor City.

OpenHack + Ybor City = OpenHack Ybor OpenHack is a meetup with a simple purpose: Code together, on anything. OpenHack works by hosting a meetup in your city that gets programmers of any experience level together to code. Find out more here: http://openhack.github.io/ Why Ybor? There's lots of great meetups going on across the Tampa/St. Pete area. I love the relaxed feel and organized chaos of OpenHack and Ybor just feels like the perfect place for this kind of event.

description.271: We love Python. We work with Python. And we have fun with Python. Come and meet py-friends, play and compete, work on your stuff, learn and build things and listen to interesting speakers.
description.272: A meetup for systems administrators, DevOps-minded folks, SaltStack customers, users and contributors. SaltStack is software used for enterprise scale infrastructure automation, cloud orchestration and application deployment and configuration management. The Salt open source software project was written in Python and according to GitHub is one of the largest and most active open source projects in the world. SaltStack is used by Web-scale IT organizations like LinkedIn, Hulu, Salesforce.com, NASA JPL, Clemson University, Photobucket, XMission, and thousands more.
description.273:
Santa Cruz Python Meetup meets on the second Tuesday of the month at Cruzio, 877 Cedar Street, Santa Cruz, CA.

Through a generous grant from the Python Software Foundation, our first six months of room rental fees are paid, so that we can deliver our program to Santa Cruz County. The PSF is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization that promotes, protects, and advances the Python programming language and community. The PSF is supported by its members, donors, volunteers, and sponsors. Please support the PSF and its mission by becoming a member.

Programs usually follow this format.

• Lightning talks. Five-minute presentations of Python topics.

• Presentations. Longer presentations of broader Python-related topics and demonstrations of projects.

• Hacking. Make use of the blazing fast wi-fi network at Cruzio to hack on projects, work through tutorials, or do some pair programming.

• Socializing. What's happening? Other local meetups, PyCon 2016 in Portland, OR.
description.274:
We are the first Irish group of the international PyLadies. Our focus is to help more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community. PyLadies Dublin also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!

Join our Google mailing list: https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/pyladies-dublin
description.275:
We love learning about different programming languages. From Object Oriented languages like Ruby or Java to Systems languages like Go or OCaml, to Logical languages like Prolog.

We focus on one language per meetup and go into enough detail to spark your interest and hopefully teach you something new.

It will be good to have a basic understanding of at least one programming language. We will recommend a (free) book for you to look at if you aren't familiar with the language or the language's concepts at the previous meetup.

We look forward to seeing you!
description.276:
Hey! Doing Django development and living in or around Vienna? Meet fellow Django hackers: Hear about their best-practices, their daily work-arounds or simply relax together – having a drink.
Despite the group name, Flask-users are highly welcome! :)

  • Meetup every two months.
  • Talks aimed at web developers with deadlines: Best-practices, your project's stack, elegant solutions  :)
  • You can find notes and summaries from previous talks at https://github.com/stephanpoetschner/django-vienna.
  • Use our mailing list django-vienna-list@meetup.com for contacting our group.
    (You have to be group member and use your meetup-registration-email when directly contacting the list. For forwarding requests address one of the organizers.)
  • Django-related job offers are welcome in our our mailing list, too.
description.277: PyHawaii is a community dedicated to the growth and use of the Python Programming Language in Honolulu, the Islands of Hawai'i and across the Pacific. Join us for tutorials, projects, mentoring, sprints and activities throughout the month. All skill levels are welcome! PyHawaii is your source for all things Python: * beginner training * advanced tradecraft * web development * data science and visualization * automation * system administration At PyHawaii, like PyCon, we are all about community, inclusivity and `ohana - so come join our meetup, where you will find friends, family and fantastic opportunities to learn, grow, contribute and advance your skills.
description.278:
Lagos Python Meetup is a weekly gathering of Python Programming Language enthusiasts in the city of Lagos. Are you a Beginner, Intermediate or Advanced Python Programmer? Join us for a night of learning, sharing, and fun – all skill levels are welcome!

Intermediate or Advanced user: meet to refactor old codes, build new libraries, contribute to open source projects and socialize.

Beginner: learn the basics of Python programming through fun weekly-structured course modules.

Come with your laptop, we'd cover pizza and soda :)
description.279:
PyLadies 是一個專屬於女生的 Python 愛好者聚會，專供喜歡 Python 的女生、想學 Python 的女生、想瞭解 Python 的女生，彼此交流、交換心得，聊天認識朋友的地方。
我們是一個國際性的 Python 交流組織，主要任務是希望透過分享、教育與會議等活動的方式幫助更多女生可以在 Python 社群中成為主動的參與者與領導者。
我們將會於每個月舉辦不同主題的活動，例如：初學者的入門、使用 Python 的應用與經驗分享，相關教學等主題。只要你是女孩並對 Python 有興趣，歡迎你來參加喔！

Pyladies is a group of women developers who love the Python programming language.
We are an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community.
We host monthly meetups around the third Saturday every month with different topics such as beginners meetups, project of python presentation and tutorial. Open to all who identify as women. Feel free to join us!
description.280: A meetup group for technology enthusiasts in and around Nagpur. If you are fascinated by any piece of technology around you, this group is meant for you. For the lack of a generalist and an agnostic technology group in Nagpur, this meetup group will facilitate regular technology meetups, hackathons and bootcamps.
description.281: Open to all those interested in Apache Cassandra, Big Data, Hadoop, Hive, Hector, NoSQL, Pig, and high scalability. Let's get together and share what we know!
description.282: Carbon Five hosts a bi-weekly, intimate hack night for developers who want to code and collaborate for a couple of hours after work. Bring your own project or work with someone else. Developers of all experience levels are welcome. We'll kick off with a very brief daily-style intro where everyone gives their name, says what they're working on and whether or not that want a hand... then we'll get our hack on. There will be at least a couple Carbon Five folks around to help out. Doors open around 6p and we'll keep hacking until 9 (sometimes later). Bring your laptop and a project to work on. We'll provide the infrastructure, food, and beverages.
description.283:
This is the Atlanta OpenStack developer Meetup. We are a group of free software developers who are passionate about working together to help make the Openstack project a success!

Can't wait for the next meetup? Join us on IRC! We hang out on Freenode at #openstack-atlanta.
description.284:
Welcome to the official RethinkDB Nashville meetup group! 

RethinkDB is the open-source database that makes it dramatically easier to build realtime apps. 

Please join us for monthly meetups to chat about new features in RethinkDB, how companies are using it in production, to share projects and everything in between. If you are interested in getting involved, please message the organizers because we'd love your help putting together events, finding speakers, venues, etc. We'll also alternate between drinkups and meetups so we can get to know others in the community. 

Find more information at rethinkdb.com and join the team at the following: 

• Twitter, Instagram - @rethinkdb

• Slack - slack.rethinkdb.com 

• IRC - #rethinkdb on Freenode 

Look forward to meeting everyone!
description.285:
Hey Northwest Arkansas Python enthusiasts--lets get together and discuss Python in business, academia, and the web! Open to developers of all experience levels in all fields; from student web developers and veteran SciPy fanatics to those simply interested in learning more about programming with Python.

We'll try to have a healthy blend of social events and more hands-on type sessions and meet at least once a month.  If you are interested in hosting an event, let Casey Kinsey know and we'll make it happen!
description.286:
PyLadiesATX is a social/professional group for lady Python enthusiasts at every experience level. Beginners are always welcome! We represent Pythonistas from a wide variety of disciplines and interest areas - full-time developers and hobbyists alike.

Unless otherwise noted, PyLadiesATX events are exclusively for PyLadies and their invited guests. We are a group for women and other gender minorities. Trans women are welcome and recognized as women. If you are a woman who enjoys learning about and writing Python, we would love to have you come join us.

PyLadiesATX is dedicated to providing a respectful, harassment-free community. Please read & follow our Code of Conduct: http://www.pyladies.com/CodeOfConduct/

-------------

description.287:

description.288: Django, Flask, Tornado, Pyramid, Bottle, whatever. If you develop web applications in Python (or want to!), this group is for you. We'll share experiences, tips, and new technologies. And hack a bit.

description.296:

Codecademy Meetups are a place where you can come to learn more about Codecademy courses and programming languages, make friends with fellow learners, and help one another as you go through your coding journey. You can be a student or a professional, any age, sex, gender, or religion. We welcome everyone to come together and learn to code in a supportive environment full of your peers. description.297:

description.299: This is a meetup for systems administrators, data center operators, DevOps-minded folks, SaltStack customers, users and contributors. description.300:

We will be organizing presentations and workshops on everything from how to use Python to control the lights in your home, to building web applications which can scale to millions of users.
description.301: If you've ever built a tech product, you know that there are many different problems to solve... from organizing client requests to planning penetration testing - and everything in between. Instead of spending weeks trying to solve a problem that another dev team has already figured out, Web Dev Labs aims to use our group as a resource to help solve problems faster and smarter.
description.302: DataScience.LA is starting a Python for Data Science meetup! While the LA data science meetup scene has been dominated by R (mainly because of the LA R meetup one of us started 5 years ago), there are a lot of data scientists using Python. Our quick survey at the LA Machine Learning/Data Science meetup a few months ago revealed that most of the meetup's members are using R or Python, with R having only a very small lead. Therefore, to serve  all these Python users we need a Python for Data Science meetup! Also check out our site datascience.la with materials from various data science meetups, interesting blog posts and much more.
description.303:

Our focus is in Selenium ( http://seleniumhq.org/ ) and topics extend through related areas of interest, such as any type of Test Automation, Agile testing, Test-Driven Development, Mobile Testing, Continuous Integration, Continuous Deployment, building maintainable automated test scripts and much more.

You can follow us on Twitter!  https://twitter.com/pdxselenium
description.304:
Calling all Portland New Relic Users! This user group is designed to foster the community and connect you with the resources & peers you need to get the most out of New Relic's software analytics suite.

Some of topics we'll discuss:
- Application Performance Monitoring
- Understanding Apdex

Each event features talks from New Relic users and pros alike, with ample time for food, drinks, networking, and discussion. This is a great opportunity to get to know and learn best practices from other New Relic users in the area. 

All New Relic users or those interested are welcome!
description.305:
Grupo asociado a python colombia para realizar dojos, reuniones y hablar de un buen lenguaje :)

description.306:
A chance to meet programmers from Nottingham and the surrounding areas to socialise and talk about all things techie.

Anyone with an interest in coding is welcome, regardless of experience, background or language preferences.

We're a very informal group, there's no structure or agenda, so please come and say hello!

Follow us on Twitter as @NottProgs (https://twitter.com/NottProgs)
description.307:
We are an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings.

PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!

description.308:
Women Who Code é uma organização global dedicada a educar e a inspirar as mulheres a buscar conhecimento e se destacar em carreiras tecnológicas. A organização alcançou em 2015, o marco de 50.000 membros em 20 países.

Somos conhecidos por nossos grupos de estudo semanais gratuitos e técnicos e eventos mensais maiores, incluindo palestras técnicas, noites de hackers, e treinamentos de carreira. Mais de 100 empresas de tecnologia , incluindo Square, Etsy, KPCB, Heroku, Yelp, e muitos outros têm promovido eventos para esta organização popular e que continua a crescer.

Programe em qualquer framework

qualquer nível de experiência

ou apenas programe para se divertir!

Programadoras e aspirantes  a programadoras são bem vindas. Traga seu laptop e uma amiga!

Os eventos são destinados a pessoas que se identificam como mulheres e estamos sempre abertas ao gênero trans. Nosso Código de Conduta aplica-se a todos os eventos executados pela organização Women Who Code, Inc.

Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. description.309: This group is a place for developers to learn more about MongoDB, an open source, document-oriented, nosql database. If you are facing challenges with MySQL or Postgres or Oracle and want to explore a more flexible, scalable alternative, please join us at one of our monthly sessions.
description.310:
Lambdaheads though new on meetup, is a group of people interested in functional programming already existing for a few years.

If you are interested in functional programming, be it beginner or expert we would be happy to meet you every second Wednesday of the month.

As of now we have some λheads doing haskell, some doing lisp in one form or another. Idris, Coq, Elm and even F# would be interesting. Of course the functional mindset is influencing many languages today C# has lambdas/anonymous functions, closures and maps/reduces as well, Java8 has them too (well not all of them), Python, Ruby, Perl allow you to use functions as first class citizen. And Javascript - some like to call it a Lisp with C syntax.

And if all of the above is nonsense to you but you are a curious mind just come and have a glance at some, who want to share the love for functional programming.

Where: At the metalab library.
When: Every second Wednesday of the month starting at 19:30.

Who: epsilonhalbe - I am the organizer and all the other λheads
description.311:
Місія

Women Who Code  -  глобальна некомерційна організація, котра призначена надихати жінок на досягнення успіху в технологічній кар'єрі, створивши глобальне співтовариство жінок у сфері технологій. Організація зросла втричі  у 2013 році і стала однією з найбільших організацій жінок-інженерів у світі.


Повноваження

Women Who Code є професійним співтовариством для жінок працюючих в IT-cфері. Ми допомагаємо жінкам продовжити технічну кар'єру, отримати нові навички та вдосконалити наявні для подальшого професійного зростання, а також надаємо середовище для вивчення, де мережа і наставники груп цінуються.

Ключові ініціативи

•  Безкоштовні технічні навчальні групи

•  Заходи організовані за участю експертів у області IТ та інвесторів

•  Hack-події

•  Кар'єра і розвиток лідерських якостей

•  Запрошуються як уже сформовані спеціалісти так  і ті, хто бажає ними стати. Візьміть з собою свій ноутбук і запросіть друга!


Підтримка Women Who Code

Пожертвування для Women Who Code  Inc. (# 46-4218859) безпосередньо впливає на нашу здатність ефективно працювати з цією зростаючою  організацією, допомагає нам створювати нові програми, які дозволять збільшити наші досягнення  і це дозволяє нам розширитися на нові міста по всьому світу даючи можливість жінкам і дівчатам продовжити кар'єру в IT-технологіях.

Події призначені для людей, які ідентифікують себе з жінками, якщо не вказано інше. Наш Кодекс поведінки пошірюється на всі події, котрі організовані за участю Women Who Code Inc.

Women Who Code (WWCode) is dedicated to providing an empowering experience for everyone who participates in or supports our community, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, ability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or socioeconomic status. Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. I started this group to facilitate the technical discussions among pythonistas, entrepreneurs, etc. Looking forward to exchanging state-of-the-art trends and technologies with everyone.
description.313: Hi to all women that are interested in developing bioinformatics tools. Try to answer to 2 easy questions to avoid misunderstandings: - why women? is because you hate men? - No, although men are weirds (kidding ... some of my best friends are men). It seems I am weird because I don't find women in this particular field of developing bioinformatics tools (see this, for instance: https://github.com/chapmanb/bcbio-nextgen#contributors. Only a few out of 23 contributors. And this is one of the most collaborative tools I know) - and ... why? maybe women don't want this ... - well, I want to know if that is true, or whether there is another cultural reason behind that. I can not find any reason why women wouldn't be interested in developing bioinformatics tools. If there is, maybe I find what it is and I can publish a Nature paper (kidding again ...) Another experience was the last hackathons of codeFest (http://www.open-bio.org/wiki/Codefest_2014), where only there were two women out of 60 people... I just don't believe that there are no more like me... I am weird but not because of working on this. So, please, if you are interested in learn how to develop tools in Bioinformatics, or you already do, but feel alone (kidding again) ... just join the meetup and help to increase woman population in this field. The idea of this group is to be a proxy to the developer community (for now men dominated) with the hope to get a great balance in the field (and hope one day this group disappears). Everybody knows that more diverse means more ... everything.
description.314: Meet other local Python Programming Language enthusiasts!
description.315:
Ce groupe s'adresse à tous les "djangonistas" de la région de Montréal, et organise mensuellement des conférences sur un sujet d'intérêt à la communauté Django. De plus, selon l'intérêt des membres, nous organiserons régulièrement une soirée de code afin de développer une idée de logiciel en licence libre.

This group brings together all of Montreal's djangonistas, and organizes a monthly conference on a subject of interest to the Django community. Also, if the members wish, we will regularly organize a night of code where we will develop an open-source project idea.
description.316:
We are an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings.

PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!
description.317:
Much of our support comes from the active DFW Data Science communities, individuals and Divergence Academy which teaches classes in Python, Hadoop, Data Visualization, and many more. You can sign up its courses and workshops at http://divergence.academy/

Divergence Academy aspires to run one of the largest Open Data Science Meetup groups in DFW area and one of the largest open data and data science group communities in the U.S. The mission is to gather data scientists and promote open data and data science by offering meetups, conferences and a weekly newsletter. 

We welcome food and drink sponsorship from any companies in the North Texas area. Thank you in advance for all your support!

Press inquiries and general inquiries contact is info@divergence.academy

Blog: http://divergence.academy/category/meetup

Twitter: @divergencedfw

 HashTag: #Scydivers
description.318:
The Houston Recreational Computer Programming Group meets on the 2nd Sunday of each month at TX/RX Labs. We aim to have a few short presentations by group members about their forays into recreational computer programming, creative coding, just generally programming computers for the fun of it. It's kind of a show and tell for programmers, a place to find out what cool little projects other programmers are working on and a place to show off your own creations. Programmers of all skill levels, from beginner to expert and using any languages from machine code, C, C++, Java, Scheme, Haskell, Lua, Javascript, or even your own home made language etc., are welcome.

What: Houston Recreational Computer Programming Group

When: 2nd Sunday of each month at 1:30pm

Where: TX/RX Labs, 205 Roberts St., Houston, TX, 77003
description.319: OpenHack, as the name implies, is an open "forum" for all software engineers in the city to come together and work on any project they like in a setting conducive to meeting new people, getting work done, and/or learning new skills. It's a great chance to get out and pair with others (or work by yourself), bounce ideas off other people, and connect with other developers in the city. Any project, any programming language, any platform, any reason - everyone who's looking to write some code (or pair program) is welcome. Take some time to work on that side project, learn a new skill, and make some new friends by coming out to OpenHack Austin.
description.320: If you have no programming experience and want to learn the Python programming language, you are invited to attend Alamo Python Learners group. If you have Python experience (all skill levels) and would like to participate and share your experience with Python newbies, you are welcome to attend as well. Meetings are held on the second and fourth Tuesday of every month at The Factory at Rackspace . Python professionals, mentors, and coaches will be booked to speak and coach at our meetings. Join us to network and discuss learning strategies, reference materials, and career goals. RSVP at least 48 hours in advance of meeting to be added to guest list. Bring your laptop and any Python learning material to share.
description.321:
Python Ireland is a group for anyone interested in learning more about the Python programming language. We aim to hold a meetup every month on a variety of topics from Computer Science, finance, research, big data and more, with a focus on  Python related technologies.

It is suitable for all levels and new people are always welcome.

We also have an annual conference in October called PyCon Ireland. If you are interested in hearing more about this conference, or our group please check out our website at http://python.ie/ and http://python.ie/pycon .
description.322:
The aim of this meetup is to promote discussion, learning and interaction around Data Science in the South West.  

This is a group for statisticians, mathematicians, programmers, data scientists, data alchemists and anyone interested in using data for analytics.  We aim to run meetings on a quarterly basis and occasionally offer free workshops.  Meetings will be informal and consist of a few short  data science related presentations followed by an opportunity to network over a drink.

We are always keen to hear from anyone interested in offering a presentation!
description.323: London Python Project Nights is a monthly event for people who code. The event's founders needed an excuse to find time to work on the ideas they always spoke about when they met at other tech events, but never found the time; they also thought this was probably a problem other developers faced, and that the added peer pressure of sharing their creations from conception would help them actually produce their projects. As a result London Python Project Nights was born. We welcome anyone who has a project idea they would like to work on, or looking for a project to contribute to. We have had people come to start a new project, people working on their existing project, people joining those of other attendees, even people coming to work alone on large well-known open source products. We do not enforce a minimum level of coding ability, but we do expect everyone to contribute on some level, and have a code of conduct we expect attendees to adhere to (http://london-python-project-nights.github.io/code-of-con...). This is intended to make the event as inclusive as possible, and suggestions for ways we can improve are welcome. TL;TR In summary we're all about code, everyone is welcome, bring your own food and drink, work on whatever you want, as long as you're willing to talk people through what you've done at the end. For information, including a write-up of our first few events, please see london-python-project-nights.github.io/events.
description.324: A group for everyone interested in functional programming languages and programming language theory. All languages welcome, including Haskell, Clojure, Elixir/Erlang, Scala, Elm, etc.
description.325: Group designed to organize Kyiv.py/Kharkiv.py/Dnepr.py/Lviv.py meetups and PyCon Ukraine conference.
description.326: We are a group of civic developers, designers, storytellers and policy leaders who are part of the Code for America Brigade network, and who contribute their skills toward using the web as a platform for local government and community service, as well as providing a skill-sharing environment to further local area tech education.
description.327:
Mission:

Women Who Code is a global nonprofit organization dedicated to inspiring women to excel in technology careers by creating a global, connected community of women in technology. The organization tripled in 2013 and has grown to be one of the largest communities of women engineers in the world.

Empowerment:

Women Who code is a professional community for women in tech. We provide an avenue for women to pursue a career in technology, help them gain new skills and hone existing skills for professional advancement, and foster environments where networking and mentorship are valued.

Key Initiatives:

Free technical study groups

Events featuring influential tech industry experts and investors

Hack events

Career and leadership development

Current and aspiring coders are welcome. 

Bring your laptop and a friend! 

Support Women Who Code:

Donating to Women Who Code, Inc. (#46-4218859) directly impacts our ability to efficiently run this growing organization, helps us produce new programs that will increase our reach, and enables us to expand into new cities around the world ensuring that women and girls everywhere have the opportunity to pursue a career in technology.

Women Who Code (WWCode) is dedicated to providing an empowering experience for everyone who participates in or supports our community, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, ability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or socioeconomic status. Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. Our Code of Conduct applies to all events run by Women Who Code, Inc. If you would like to report an incident or contact our leadership team, please submit an incident report form.

WomenWhoCode.com

Twitter | Facebook
description.328: We are a group of coders in the Asheville area working in different languages and with different technologies with a commitment to being excellent at what we do. We have a mailing list as well: https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups=#!forum/asheville-coders
description.329:
This is a meetup for {Cmd, Jl, R, Py, Matlab} Stan users. The plan is to have talks, Q & A sessions, and workshops.

Stan (http://mc-stan.org) is a probabilistic programming language implementing full Bayesian statistical inference with 

• MCMC sampling (NUTS, HMC)

and penalized maximum liklelihood estimation with

•  Optimization (L-BFGS)

Stan is coded in C++ and runs on all major platforms (Linux, Mac, Windows).

Stan is freedom-respecting, open-source software (new BSD core, GPLv3 interfaces).

Many thanks to R Studio for their support of the meetup group.
