Our goal is to open, improve, and engage local governments and community outreach programs within the Tallahasee area to pursue effective, sustainable technology solutions that solve real problems. If you can write code we need you, but we also need Innovators, community organizers, business professionals, legal researchers, bloggers/marketers, technology/gadget aficionados, software/usability testers, educators/trainers, artists/designers, students, government employees, people with non-profit experience; regardless of your indivdual skills and talents, if you're a U.S. citizen with a passion for solving community problems, we need you!
description.333:
Meet other local Python Programming Language enthusiasts!

We use the TampPy Bay google group for our discussion forum. (We've had trouble not getting emails from meetup). So please also join the discussion group at http://groups.google.com/group/tampybay.
description.334:
Meet other developers and ops engineers using Docker. Docker is an open platform for developers and sysadmins to build, ship, and run distributed applications. Consisting of Docker Engine, a portable, lightweight runtime and packaging tool, and Docker Hub, a cloud service for sharing applications and automating workflows, Docker enables apps to be quickly assembled from components and eliminates the friction between development, QA, and production environments. As a result, IT can ship faster and run the same app, unchanged, on laptops, data center VMs, and any cloud.

Learn more about Docker at http://www.docker.com
description.335:
We're open for all forms of hacking. Software and hardware. If you are software developer, engineer, or tinkerer of technology, you are welcome to join us.

www.hacknite.com
description.336: Django Barranquilla es una comunidad para todos los interesados en desarrollar aplicaciones en Django dentro de la ciudad de Barranquilla. Los invito a que se unan y participen. Esperamos poder contar con ustedes y crear una sana comunidad en la ciudad. Están invitados!
description.337: PyLadies is an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings. PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!
description.338: We would like to bring together like minded folks to discuss and engage in dialogue around DevOps and all related features. What IS DevOps now? Where is it heading? What is causing the shift? Focusing on the East Bay market, and what companies are spearheading it, which tools are being used, and where we all fit in.
description.339:
Calling all open data and transparency activists to join us every last Wednesday of the month for liberating data and lightening talks. Whether you can write a few lines of code to write a bot, or a journalist who is interested in covering stories on transparency, or a campaigner who champions an open and free world - come along to meet like-minded people and use open data to change the world.

If you are an NGO who would like to suggest a mission for these meetups - do get in touch at hera@opencorporates.com

Powered by missions.opencorporates.com // OpenCorporates
description.340: Software developers getting together to swap stories, build things and learn from each other. We mix talks and social sessions and welcome all levels of skill and experience; if you are interested in making software, you'll find something useful here!
description.341:
PyLadies Amsterdam is a group for Python female programmers at any level of experience from Amsterdam Area. Pyladies is an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings.

PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!

We only have one condition:  the number of women at our meetups should be a least 50%. So, bring a nice lady with you if you can :-)
description.342:
PyGrunn is the 'Python and friends' conference with a local footprint and global mindset. Firmly rooted in the open source culture it aims to provide the leading lights in advanced internet technologies a platform to inform, inspire and impress their peers.
This is the Meetup page of PyGrunn where all meetings will be announced as well. The general PyGrunn site will always be pygrunn.org and the community can be found on Google+ (https://plus.google.com/u/0/communities/100366363140062149...).
description.343:
Programmieren in Python für Interessierte aller Erfahrungsstufen.

Wenn Du mit uns in Kontakt treten möchtest, schreib bitte an unsere Mailingliste, oder schau im IRC vorbei (#pyugat auf freenode) statt Meetup.com!

Mehr Informationen auf: http://pyug.at/ .

Programming in Python for all experience levels.

If you want to contact us, please use our mailing list or come by on IRC (#pyugat on freenode) instead of meetup.com!

More info: http://pyug.at/ .
description.344:
We are Python Philippines, a community in the Philippines for enthusiasts and users of the Python programming language, who aim to expand our network of people, opportunities and ideas.

The group started back in 2007 when Jun Auza of Tech Source blogged about forming a local Python User's Group. JM Maranan stumbled upon the post and created a Google group.
description.345:
This is a group for professional developers and users of the Python programming language in New Zealand to expand our network of people, opportunities and ideas.

We have monthly meetings with presentations - if you're interested, please join the group and check out our website for further information.

This meetup.com group is for Auckland meetings.
description.346:
This is a group for professional developers and users of the Python programming language in New Zealand to expand our network of people, opportunities and ideas.

We have monthly meetings with presentations - if you're interested, please join the group and check out our website for further information.

This meetup.com group is for Wellington meetings.
description.347:
Welcome to the Australian OpenStack User Group. We are passionate about working together to help make the OpenStack project a success.

Presently this is an "Umbrella Group" for OpenStack user groups in:

Sydney
Melbourne
Brisbane
Adelaide
Perth
Hobart
Canberra

If you are keen to start a group in your area or help with organising in the above locations, please email us at info@openstack.org.au

We now have a youtube channel at https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC8RHLWC21s...

(It is possible that this group will one day split out to city based groups as the community grows, however, due to the inability of the MeetUp site administrators to accommodate some simple and considerate flexibility in their interface it means only a fixed and limited selection of cities is available, so we cannot bind this user group to a generic "Australia" location.)
description.348:
Linux Users of Victoria is one of Australia's largest GNU/Linux, free software and open source user groups. We conduct two regular events in Melbourne each month. On the first Tuesday of the month LUV runs technical lectures at 200 Victoria St. Carlton VIC 3053 and at VPAC's Training (RMIT Bldg 91, 110 Victoria St. Carlton VIC 3053), on the third Saturday of the month, LUV runs a hands on workshop, addressing the issues of the users who turn up. The workshops have a "beginners" level talk, whereas the technical lectures are for an "intermediate" and "advanced" audience.  LUV has four regional chapters in Ballarat, Geelong, LaTrobeValley and Shepparton.  Many of our members also attend Melbourne Linux Users Group (MLUG).

Who should join?

Anyone is welcome to join.  You just need to have an interest in Linux and/or Open Source Software in general.   Even if you don't, you are still welcome!
description.349: A group for men, women, and children interested in the Python programming language. Talks, sprints, socials, and other events will eventually fill our calendar, so stay tuned!
description.350:
This is the meetup page for Python programming language user group for the Piedmont Triad of North Carolina, USA (PYthon Piedmont Triad User Group, or PYPTUG). Our website is http://pyptug.org and we invite you to come and join us to learn more about the Python programming language, modules and tools. All skills levels are welcome. Python is the perfect language to learn if you've never programmed before, and at the other end, it is also the perfect tool that no expert would do without. 

It plays nice with C/C++, C# (Iron Python), Java (Jython), Javascript (Brython), Perl, R, etc. and it scales well (our members use Python on the credit card size Raspberry Pi computer, up to large scale cloud deployments).

The official group discussion list is at: https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#!for...
description.351: This is a group for people interested in bioinformatic applications, either as researcher or a programmer. The Kansas City area has a large concentration of biotechnology companies and institutions doing amazing and diverse work. I'm hoping this group will give people a chance to meet others in this field. We'll meet once a month after work for a happy hour to see how everyone is doing and to discuss projects, interests, or whatever. I want to help grow the bioinformatic community in KC, and I think a little face-to-face time would do us all wonders.
description.352: The Austin Apache Spark community is exploding. Join us for a monthly show and tell of the latest use cases.
description.353: Nevada County's programmers, software developers, and scalable tech business founders are getting together for hackathons, help, support, and fun. Join us, meet other local developers, build something great, and become a part of Nevada County's tech heritage.
description.354: On a Hackternoon - a SVBBDev Meetup group, Mobile meets Web meets Cloud, cross platform BlackBerry Developers hack and have fun together. Use this Meetup to fill gaps in your personal tech stack. This Meetup has a strong educational focus through project deployment. We learn by watching, asking, listening, and doing. We use a combo of Paired Programming, brain power, and a project deployment to help you stay caught up.  Usually we meet at a WIFI cafe or a co-working location like Ground Floor, Hacker Dojo, or NextSpace.
description.355: Love to build amazing things quick? Then you've found the right place. Bay Area Hackathons are hosted at Bay Area companies and a are a great way to meet new people, build amazing things, and win killer prizes.
description.356:
We get together once a month to talk about anything related to the Python programming language.

Our aim is to enable people like you to develop a toolkit to get stuff done. We hope to attract a wide range of ability levels so as to facilitate a pipeline that develops capable Pythonistas.

Anyone who is interested in Python is welcome, whatever your level of knowledge (we're very happy to help with questions from those just learning the language), and for whatever purpose you use it.
description.357:
Wir sind ein bunter Haufen von Selbständige, Angestellte, Projektleiter, Softwareentwickler etc und treffen uns einmal im Monat in Duisburg.

Wir trinken etwas, essen etwas und quatschen dabei völlig planlos, also ohne eine Tagesordnung oder etwas in dieser Richtung, über verschiedene Themen aus der IT-Welt - vornehmlich aus dem Bereich Softwareentwicklung, aber auch Off-Topic.

Häufige Themen: Objective C, Java, Python, PHP, Neue Geräte, Hardware Projekte, Projektmanagement, Webentwicklung
description.358:
PyLadies is an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings. PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for women and a bridge to the larger Python world. Anyone with an interest in Python is encouraged to participate!

Pyladies Berlin are regularly meeting once per month, every second Tuesday of the month. There is usually a talk and a hands on session over a python topic. Anyone is welcome to propose topics that wishes to learn and give a talk.
description.359:
Olá, se você veio até aqui, ficamos felizes!

Esse é um dos canais para discutirmos sobre desenvolvimento Open Source, queremos que esses encontros sejam além de tecnologias; esperamos que ele forneça apoio à todos em diversos segmentos e vertentes; seja parte disso e ajude a comunidade Open-Sanca para que este Meetup ganhe força, não importa se você é iniciante, ninja-samurai ou Goku das profundezas do Egeu.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Afinal, o que a comunidade espera de você desenvolvedor? Quando você ouve a palavra contribua, espera-se que possamos ir além de githubs, palestras, workshops e afins, por isto você é uma peça importante no mundo, contribua!

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Queremos fazer um bate papo no qual todos possam colaborar e  fomentar um networking com empresas, desenvolvedores, comunidades acadêmicas, afinal hoje praticamente o que todos falam é sobre tecnologia e inovação.

Faça parte do Open-Sanca, traga seus amigos, independente da carreira que segue, todos podem colaborar, abaixo enumeramos alguns assuntos que achamos ser pertinentes, mas fique a vontade para apontar tópicos que você julgar válido também, afinal estamos falando sobre ser OPEN:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tópicos:

- Oferecer Palestras 
- Oferecer Workshops 
- Minicursos
- Desenvolvimento de software adotando as principais linguagens e tecnologias do mercado Open Source como Python, Groovy, Ruby, Embarcados, JavaScript, Android, IOS e etc
-  Fornecer condições para que Startups possam ser encontradas e angariadas por desenvolvedores, investidores e afins....

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Esperamos vocês!  ;)

The focus will be on Django and web application design, development and deployment. Python will obviously be an underlining theme, but there are specific python groups focused on python solely (see: http://sypy.eventbrite.com/ and www.sypy.org).
description.364: We are a group of Systems Engineers and DevOps folks who want to Ansible all the things. Want to learn more about Ansible? Come join us. Already know Ansible well? Come share your knowledge.
description.365:
This is a group for anyone interested in 'BIG DATA' and 'The Internet of Things'. If you're in IT then chances are you're working with some form of data and possibly Big Data.

We have rebranded from "Data Science Adelaide" to "Big Data Adelaide" to cover a range of areas for anyone working with Data. So if you deal with something generally related to converting data into useful insights then you will hopefully benefit from joining the group.

Whether you’re in business, academia, government or health and whether you’re an analyst, data miner, programmer, student, electrical engineer, computer scientist, physicist, etc, and you work with data to generate insights, build predictive models, build optimisation models, build reports / dashboards / visualisations, automate analyses, etc, using python, R, SQL, C/C+, Java, Excel, Hadoop, etc, and you care about doing it right, efficiently, repetitively, optimally, visually, etc, then join us!

We plan to meet up every month or so. The meetups will probably take the format of knowledge exchange, where speakers will tell us about their tools/techniques/experience/mistakes - to hopefully introduce new ideas and technology that others can add to their toolbox.

We will also have speakers from VC, Government and something different thrown in now and then to make it exciting.

There will generally be Pizza and some form of tasty beverage with a small donation to cover costs. A venue will be notified soon, and we plan on holding an event by mid-October.

(Most of this description is borrowed from Data Science Melbourne, we couldn’t say it better ourselves!)
description.366: Curious about data science but don't know where to start? Come to our meetup! Our hands-on workshops will introduce you to a variety of cool concepts like machine learning, data mining, version control, data visualization, etc. And yes, you will become confident with using awesome programming languages like Python and R.
description.367:
This group is for people who want to become full stack developers and "maybe" entrepreneurs or Full stackers. First join our slack chat group at the link below:  

ottawafullstack.herokuapp.com

Full stack means you want to know front-end development, design, programming, infrastructure (servers/ cloud, virtual machines), databases, programming frameworks and everything in between AND maybe also some of other things that people should know about building a company. such as, how to build a good cap table, or what SDR is, or how much equity to give to whom, The group will regularly be engaging in "Tracks" on full stack programs that take you through all of these and some other fun stuff we'll think of ourselves. We are entering a future where many of us will be self-employed or operate with partners or crowds towards common goals. You may have also heard of terms such as "full stack marketer" or "the stack" in referring to all the elements that make a software program work or the "sales stack". We'll examine those as well. Anyway, no one is going to look out for you more than you and so it's important to be generalists as well as specialists. A generalist is the ultimate specialist because they much more self-reliant than others. Join us you know you want to :). Take that plunge. HIT JOIN DO IT RIGHT NOW !!!!! .
description.368:
CoderDojo McDonough is a free program brought to you by developers in Henry County. CoderDojo is a worldwide non-profit group founded to teach young people (ages 7-17) to code.  Our sessions are located at the McDonough Public Library and are open to all Henry County youth and parents/guardians.

Please consider mentoring!  We are seeking developers at all skill levels who are interested in mentoring local youth at CoderDojo McDonough.  Please signup to be a volunteer or mentor here: http://www.coderdojohenry.com/MentorSignup

The Henry County Library System has partnered with SimplePhoto and VersionOne to sponsor CoderDojo McDonough. The organizers of CoderDojo McDonough are working closely with the VersionOne employees who coordinate CoderDojo Ponce Springs in Atlanta.

Important note: you must be a parent or older than 18 to sign up on this meetup site:
 This site is for parents or people over the age of 18 to help us with events and to see how many people to expect at events. If you are under the age of 18, you may not sign up on this site or RSVP for events. Instead, you must have your parent or 18+ guardian do so for you. More importantly, your parent or 18+ guardian must attend all events with you. This is in accordance with Meetup and Coder Dojo policies.
description.369:
Meeting fellow Developers, Techies and UberCoders in the local area but outside work can be cumbersome. Local HN meetups become a "who's who" of the local tech community. We can learn from each other, do some interesting projects, recruit, get recruited or at the very least have a seriously geeky conversation with others who actually understand what we're saying!

We, coders/hackers, are a special group of people. We're creative, smart and best of all, we generally love what we do and are in the unique position to influence our world in ways previously unfathomable. If we come together, great things may happen!

The idea is simple, we have a very informal get-together at local place with WiFi, enjoy some coffee/appetizers and discuss new technologies, projects, local tech news etc.
description.370: Lawrence Coders brings together a mix of professional software developers, students and hobbyists to discuss all aspects of programming, development and design. We're located in Lawrence, Kansas, and welcome discussion of all languages and platforms.
description.371: Short talks by experts in various areas of interest to small businesses, entrepreneurs and freelancers, followed by questions and answers. Meetings will be from one to two hours long starting at 10:30 or 11:30. Bring a lunch if you'd like and we'll supply the coffee and tea and interesting speakers.
description.372: This is a laid-back meetup for anyone interested in functional programming (whatever that means for you). We have a monthly meeting to hang out and talk about software development, programming techniques, specific language features, or anything else of interest related to functional programming. Everyone is welcome, no experience is necessary, and deep curiosity is greatly encouraged.
description.373:
Riverside Raspberry in a Nutshell

So what is this Raspberry Pi thing anyway?  Well the Raspberry Pi is a small computer on a printed circuit board, costing around $35.  Its stated primary goal is to spark kids’ interest in computer programming, but it has shown a huge appeal to both kids and adults with other interests such as electronics, robotics, and open source software.  It has a good balance of reasonable power, an open design, and a very low cost that makes it a great platform for experimenting on.  This group will appeal to thinkers and tinkerers, the scientifically curious, software developers looking to get into embedded development, or anyone young or old that has a knack for tech in general.  The purpose of Riverside Raspberry is to share knowledge related to the Raspberry Pi device specifically, and to promote interest in tech development in the Inland Empire in general.  The group is currently meeting the 2nd Monday evening of every month.

To find out more about the Raspberry Pi computer in general, you can start with http://www.raspberrypi.org/
description.374: Part talks, part sharing, part support group. /dev/reno is an environment where new and experienced programmers come to meet other developers and learn about new technologies as well as time-tested patterns for getting the job done. Are you a programmer living or working in the Reno area? Have a talk we'd love to hear? Have a harrowing experience related to a programming language or environment? Just want to have a listen? Come spend an hour or two with us every month. We would love to meet you!
description.375:
We are people who do fun things with data.  

We are a group of people who want to develop a breadth of knowledge and skills. 

We are people of all skill levels, from people getting started programming to data science gurus.

We are a group of people who do super happy fun data projects together.
description.376:
MISSION

To connect, support, and inspire a diverse group of local technical learners to excel in technology careers through a programming language agnostic study group.

KEY INITIATIVES

• Free technical study groups

• Online mentoring and code review

• Hack events

• Career and leadership development

MODE

The general focus of the group will be on solving problems from exercism.io and ProjectEuler. 

Exercism.io is a platform that provides weekly code problems in a variety of programming languages, but teaches you to solve the problems by using a test-driven approach, and by participating in code review. This is really important practice if you want to have a job as a developer. 

WHO SHOULD ATTEND

We welcome many levels of attendees:

• Brand new beginners**

• Coders new to a particular language

• Experienced developers 

• Anyone in between

**If you have ZERO experience writing code, but want to learn, please please PLEASE make sure to come to the Setupfest! events, so that we can help you get set up and on your way!

EEK, I'M SCARED

If you don't know what "test-driven" or "code review" means, that's OK! That's what this group is for. Organizers and core team members will be present to help you with questions, and will be the ones reviewing your code and offering feedback.

"Getting feedback on your code" might sound intimidating if you are brand new -- but you can be confident that it's actually a really good thing. 

CODE OF CONDUCT

Our Code of Conduct that can be summarized as "Be excellent with each other." This applies to all levels of communication within the group, including attendees and organizers, during face-to-face events, interactions in code review, and beyond.
description.377:
PyBelfast is a group for anyone interested in learning more about the Python programming language. We aim to hold a meetup every other month on a variety of topics, with a focus on Python related technologies.

It is suitable for all levels and new people are always welcome.
description.378:
PyDiff holds monthly meetups in Cardiff for anyone who uses or wants to learn about Python.

Everyone's welcome, from experienced programmers to new learners, wherever their interest lies.

Feel free to jump in our gitter room to chat: https://gitter.im/PyDiff/PyDiff.github.io
description.379: The Euregio Tech Meetup offers monthly events, where members gather to hear leading-edge thinking on technology topics, and build their networks to develop their businesses. We aspire to be a community that helps each other, is proud to produce services made in the Euregio area, provides knowledge to peers and becomes an integral part of the local economy.
description.380:
pyCologne ist die lokale Python User Group der Kölner Region. Die User Group bietet allen Python-Interessierten Raum und Gelegenheit, sich über Python auszutauschen und voneinander zu lernen. Zu den regelmäßigen monatlichen Treffen kommen Teilnehmer aus dem gesamten Großraum Köln-Bonn-Düsseldorf. Die Teilnehmer halten Vorträge, berichten Neuigkeiten und bieten Hilfe für Python-Einsteiger und –Profis. Daneben stellen die Teilnehmer regelmäßig neue Bücher vor. Die Treffen sind offen für jeden und neue Gesichter sind jederzeit herzlich willkommen!

pyCologne is the local Python User Group of Cologne. The user group offers space and opportunity for all those interested in Python to share knowledge and learn about Python. At regular monthly meetups people from the whole area Cologne-Bonn-Düsseldorf participate. The participants hold talks, share news, and provide help for both Python newbies and professionals. The meetups are open for everybody and new faces are very welcome to join!

Web: http://pycologne.de
description.381:

Am zweiten Montag im Monat findet eine Input-Session statt. Hier laden wir externe Referentinnen ein, stellen selbst Technologien und Konzepte vor oder arbeiten Projekt übergreifend zusammen.

description.382: A group of engineers and artists involved or interested in web development, programming languages, frameworks and tools. We'll meet once a month for talks and some beer afterward.
description.383: This group is about all aspects of data management, analysis and visualization with a focus on Python tooling. The goal is to have regular lesson learned sessions and tutorials for the Munich Python|Data community.
description.384: Vienna.pm is a group to bring together people interested in Perl, related languages, ecosystems and fun. Everyone who is interested in latest Perl related developments or just wants to join us as part of the social meets is welcome. Meetings are happening on a monthly basis.
description.385:
We believe that the internet is a tool that can make society better -- and that it is under threat from mass surveillance, corporatisation and censorship.

Can we expect tools like Enigmail and pidgin-otr to be adopted by the general public as they stand today, when they are difficult even for professional technologists to use?

This group will provide a space where we can work together to improve tools like these.

We are developers and technologists. We have the power and the responsibility to make digital privacy easier and more common.
description.386:
Meet other developers and ops engineers using Docker. Docker is an open platform for developers and sysadmins to build, ship, and run distributed applications. Consisting of Docker Engine, a portable, lightweight runtime and packaging tool, and Docker Hub, a cloud service for sharing applications and automating workflows, Docker enables apps to be quickly assembled from components and eliminates the friction between development, QA, and production environments. As a result, IT can ship faster and run the same app, unchanged, on laptops, data center VMs, and any cloud.

Learn more about Docker at http://www.docker.com
description.387:
A meetup for anyone interested in the Python programming language.  All skill levels are welcome.  :)

Our initial focus will be on monthly meetings for discussing various Python related topics.  I hope to eventually expand our group to include training & education opportunities, project nights, and workshops.

Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions about DerbyPy. 

Hope to see you around!

DerbyPy Organizer
description.388:
Join the Odoo Montreal Meetup Group to discuss the application, the Quebec community, the integrators, the case studies, latest news, coding practices, implementation methodology,... This group is open to existing and prospective users and integrators, business applications enthusiasts, technical and functional consultants, Python developers and open source fans. This meetup is an open initiative of Savoir-faire Linux and Microcom.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hR5fKO84k1o

La communauté de pratique Odoo (anciennement OpenERP) se réunit deux fois par mois à Montréal. Ces rencontres visent à favoriser le développement des connaissances techniques et fonctionnelles et à augmenter l'intérêt commercial des entreprises de la région envers cette solution informatique aux potentiels immenses.

Les rencontres sont divisés en deux rencontres mensuelles en alternance. La première permet d’apprendre sur les capacités  fonctionnelles de Odoo et la seconde permet aux personnes désirant développer sur cette plateforme d’approfondir et de partager leurs connaissances.

Odoo est une suite progicielle de gestion d'entreprise intégrée, ouverte et publiée sous licence AGPL. Elle comprend pas moins de 700 modules applicatifs pour la gestion des ventes, de la relation client (CRM), la gestion de projet, la gestion d'entrepôt, la production, la comptabilité, les ressources humaines, etc. Cette robuste plateforme de gestion est développée, animée et supportée par la firme Odoo S.A., qui est son éditeur officiel. Cette compagnie est basée à Bruxelles avec des antennes au Luxembourg, en Inde et aux USA, et est assistée d'une communauté de 1500 individus et 400 entreprises répartis dans 70 pays, dont une dizaine au Canada.

Few URL / Quelques liens :

Odoo

OCA, The Odoo Community Association

The Canadian Page on OCA

The Canadian Team on Github
description.389: This is a group for anyone interested in topics related to machine learning. description.390:
#IntroToCoding is simple. Free coding lessons, food and drinks! 

Everyone interested in learning to code, is invited. Learn from the best teachers and mentors and the most modern technologies: PHP, HTML5, CSS, NodeJs, Python, Wordpress, iOS, Android and much more.

Because coding is not only about programming languages, you would also "learn how to learn", UI/UX, design patterns, SCRUM and programming methodologies and techniques, etc. And finally, listen stories and experiences by the top programmers in the city. 

All attendees will be receiving a 3.000 discount in tuition in 4Geeks Academy courses. 4Geeks Academy is a series of coding bootcamps with 10 weeks of fully immerse and hands-on program. We are the first code school training programmers to thrive within a specialized industry: Marketing industry, Smart-City, Gaming, etc. Positioning them as high-ranked job candidates as they fulfill the needs of programing in traditional industries. Want to learn how to code? Come with us and start a career in programming, get hired and rise you income!
description.391:
Mission:

Women Who Code is a global nonprofit organization dedicated to inspiring women to excel in technology careers by creating a global, connected community of women in technology. The organization tripled in 2013 and has grown to be one of the largest communities of women engineers in the world.

Empowerment:

Women Who code is a professional community for women in tech. We provide an avenue for women to pursue a career in technology, help them gain new skills and hone existing skills for professional advancement, and foster environments where networking and mentorship are valued.

Key Initiatives:

Free technical study groups

Events featuring influential tech industry experts and investors

Hack events

Career and leadership development

Current and aspiring coders are welcome. 

Bring your laptop and a friend! 

Support Women Who Code:

Donating to Women Who Code, Inc. (#46-4218859) directly impacts our ability to efficiently run this growing organization, helps us produce new programs that will increase our reach, and enables us to expand into new cities around the world ensuring that women and girls everywhere have the opportunity to pursue a career in technology.

Women Who Code (WWCode) is dedicated to providing an empowering experience for everyone who participates in or supports our community, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, ability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or socioeconomic status. Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. Our Code of Conduct applies to all events run by Women Who Code, Inc. If you would like to report an incident or contact our leadership team, please submit an incident report form.

WomenWhoCode.com

Twitter | Facebook

Proporcionamos una vía para que sigan una carrera relacionada con tecnologías, ayudándoles a obtener nuevas habilidades y pulir las ya existentes para su desarrollo profesional, así como proveer un ambiente en donde el networking y las mentorías son valorados.

Our Code of Conduct applies to all events run by Women Who Code, Inc. If you would like to report an incident or contact our leadership team, please submit an incident report form.

womenwhocode.com

Twitter | Facebook
description.395:
This Meetup is for beginners in data science who have a background in quantitative fields. Most of us know linear algebra, ODE's, PDE's, statistics and have solved many other equations. What we need to learn is analytics, in a business setting where success and failure is measured by how money you made or saved the company.

Big Data, small data and medium data all have a place in this field we call data science. In this group I tend to focus on small data because it's the most common. Medium is next and big data lastly. 

Members have an opportunity to lead presentations. This is a great way to get the most out of your last Kaggle competition. Bring it to us, and in the process of preparation you'll probably review the whole thing much more. Then learn from the group.

This group is also about learning how to iterate quickly by hacking, good object oriented programming, our love of theory, and the demand for business acumen. These subjects are absolutely the inverse of each other and yet we must bring them together in our quest to become a data scientist.

Cheers,

dpc
description.396:
Calling all coding wise guys! 

Join our regular 'Code and Cannoli' evenings in Rotterdam for interesting sessions by expert speakers while enjoying great Italian food, drinks and catching up with colleague developers. Each 'Code and Cannoli' evening has its own theme based around Web, Mobile or Security. All skills levels are welcome. 

Attendance is free of charge. 

The evenings are hosted by DevMob at Schiedamsedijk 50 in Rotterdam.
description.397:
Aquest és un grup per qualsevol persona interessada en la tecnologia web moderna, en sistemes, experiència d'usuari en la web i desenvolupaments per mòbils. La iniciativa dels cafè amb web van neixer el 2013 per ser un punt de trobada de gent vinculada en el mon de la web, el desenvolupament i les noves tecnologies. La idea es compartir i explorar.

Les xerrades del CafèAmbWeb poden parlar de qualsevol tema al relacionat amb la web, i estan orientades a un públic ben divers, però sobretot estan pensades per desenvolupadors, dissenyadors i emprenedors. Les xerrades duren entre 15-20 minuts i tracten temes tant de forma introductòria (exemple: "Principis del disseny gràfic") com especialitzada (exemple: "Gestió de localstorage en HTML5"). No t'obsessionis amb la idea d'agradar a tot el públic; si vols parlar d'alguna cosa avançada, fes-ho sense por.

Si vols participar com a ponent en un #cafèambweb, envia'ns un correu a vine@cafeambweb.cat. Revisa abans els últims #cafèambweb, per si el tema del que vols parlar ja ha sortit (encara que sempre pots donar-hi un enfocament diferent).

Recorda que és molt important respectar la durada màxima de la xerrada (15-20 minuts) i tot i que no és pecat parlar de la teva empresa o negoci, l'objectiu és transmetre una idea, no convertir la xerrada en un espai publicitari.

En els #cafèambweb disposem d'un projector "amateur". No sol haver-hi massa bona wifi, així que no hi confiïs cegament per plantejar la teva xerrada. Compta sempre amb el públic de l'última fila a l'hora de dissenyar la teva presentació (lletra gran i poc text). Durant la teva presentació, tingues en compte també que hauràs de vocalitzar bé i parlar fort perquè se't senti (no, no sempre tenim un micròfon disponible).

Gràcies per la teva ajuda! El #cafèambweb ho fem entre tots :-)
description.398: Meetup do PUG-PE para mais detalhes acesse: https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/pug-pe http://pycon.pug.pe
description.399:
Modiin Tech Talks is a meeting place for people interested in all areas for development. We give presentations, run Hackathons, and discuss relevant topics.


The group had a few meetings in 2014, but we started to use Meetup only in May 2015.

Our primary location for meetings is going to be at MESH in Modiin.
description.400:
Welcome to the Greater Hartford Python Group!

Learn Python.

Or, learn more Python.

Join us and become a more effective software architect and developer!

Welcome to the Greater Hartford Python Group--where you will meet fellow software and Python enthusiasts and professionals--as we work to build and strengthen the community of software architects and developers; Python and Python-based application developers, architects and designers; and other computing technologists in Connecticut.

Python is a fun, powerful, yet easy-to-learn programming language that is used in a wide variety of application domains in industry, and is increasingly a language of choice in computer science education due to its clear, readable syntax, natural expressiveness and versatility.

Join our group as a newcomer to Python or as an accomplished Pythonista. We hope that your participation in our group will help you and others to increase their understanding of what Python can do, the best practices to apply when using Python and Python-based tools, and generally, how to be a more productive, more effective and more knowledgeable software architect and developer.

Please do not hesitate to share your ideas with us and help steer our group towards becoming an invaluable source of information and networking opportunities.  We hope you will find our group to be a passionate and fun group which is enthusiastic to grow and help all those interested in Python and software development--beginners, journeymen and experts--by sharing our collective knowledge, expertise, experiences and ideas.

Over the past few years, I have focused my attention on Python. I have started this group to share my knowledge and experience and to learn from other Pythonistas. My background includes a wide range of expertise as a computer scientist with experience in academia and industry in a number of application areas (computer graphics, design automation, computer aided design, computer architecture, programming languages and web development).

My passion is the exploration and education of computer science, computing technologies, software development and innovative software applications. I find computing and software fun, intriguing, intuitive, educational beyond its surface technology and fulfilling, and I'd like many more to experience computer science and software development in that way whether they are enthusiasts or professionals.

With this meetup, I would like to hold monthly meetups with short and long presentations by group members; study different Python practices, techniques, libraries, frameworks and applications; perhaps, create an open source application as part of the group's activities; and, perhaps, seek out financial sponsors to help attract speakers from outside of the area. I plan to offer introductory and advanced workshops on Python and Python-based applications, and to connect the group with book publishers so that we can offer door prizes to meeting attendees.

I'd enjoy hearing any ideas you may have to offer. I'm looking forward to meeting you at our next meetup.

Mark Friedman, Organizer

The Greater Hartford Python Group
description.401:
Our focus is on how to make powerful and maintainable Javascript frontends.

One of the areas of interest is "Big Data" analytics and the effective visualization of large data sets.

The format will be conversational and based on a centering theme.

Technologies that will be discussed:

  • Client application organization (Require.js, Aura.js)
  • Client visualization and data manipulation (D3.js, Crossfilter.js)
  • Analytics (Cascalog)
  • Databases (Redis, ElephantDB, HBase, MongoDB)
  • Operations (Chef)
  • Anything interesting that comes up during discussion

Topics for discussion will be warmly welcomed.
description.402:
Welcome! This is a group surrounding the new round of CincyPy meetups. We are hoping to get this group active again and encourage the use of Python and Python related technologies in the Cincinnati development scene.

Our slack channel is https://cincypy.slack.com/

We can be found on Google Groups at http://groups.google.com/group/cincypy
description.403: Let's get together to drink coffee, write code, and talk about technology.
description.404:
The worlds of hackers and journalists are coming together as reporting goes digital and Internet companies become media empires.

Journalists call themselves "hacks," someone who can churn out words in any situation. Hackers use the digital equivalent of duct tape to whip out code. Hacker-journalists try and bridge the two worlds.

This group is to bring all these people together -- those who are working to help people make sense of their world. It's for hackers exploring technologies to filter and visualize information, and for journalists who use technology to find and tell stories. In the age of information overload, all their work has become even more crucial.

This group aims to help members find inspiration and think in new directions, bringing together potential collaborators for projects and new ventures.

Please also check out our blog at http://hackshackers.com

ATL tweets via @HacksHackersATL

Help us build the future of media!
description.405:
A group of women in the Atlanta area, who are, or aspire to be developers and learn/work in the python programming language. Members of any experience level are welcome, so long as they are female. More info can be found at our google group: https://groups.google.com/group/womenspyatl

NOTE: Please bring a laptop to the meetings, if you have one. If you don't have one, bring some note-taking materials, as we will be working through tutorials at times. We will post materials online after the meetups, however if you can follow along during the meeting, the better!

We're also on twitter! @PyLadiesATL

NB: This is a group for *women* who ARE or DESIRE to be programmers. We are NOT a general 'women in tech' group. There are lots of those on meetup.com and in the Atlanta area. Please note the group will be focused on programming in python.
description.406:

The participants hold talks, share news, and provide help for both Python newbies and professionals. The meetups are open for everybody and new faces are very welcome to join!

PyBasel ist die lokale Python User Group der Region Nordwestschweiz. Die User Group bietet allen Python-Interessierten Raum und Gelegenheit, sich über Python auszutauschen und voneinander zu lernen. Die Teilnehmenden halten Vorträge, berichten Neuigkeiten und bieten Hilfe für Python-Einsteiger und -Profis. Die Treffen sind offen für jeden und neue Gesichter sind jederzeit herzlich willkommen!  

Twitter: @PyBasel
description.416: We're hosting a monthly meetup for web developers and web designers in the region of St. Pölten. There'll be ligthning talks and presentations about various web-related topics and trends, and, naturally, discussions about which text-editor is the best :) All skill levels and all types of technologies are welcome. Looking forward to meeting you!
description.417: A meetup all about Docker. Tips, tricks, best practices, deployment, scaling.
description.418: Grupo de interesse sobre OpenShift, uma plataforma como serviço open-source. O objetivo do grupo é discutir a adoção de PaaS, trocar experiências de desenvolvimento dentro de plataformas. Gostaríamos de ver no grupo desenvolvedores, empresas, blogueiros, lojas de e-commerce e até mesmo pessoas que queiram implantar sua própria nuvem privada.
description.419: Nós da Pyladies Rio pretendemos incentivar o interesse de mulheres em TI, sua participação e contribuição nas comunidades e projetos de código aberto.
description.420:
Mission:

Women Who Code is a global nonprofit organization dedicated to inspiring women to excel in technology careers by creating a global, connected community of women in technology. The organization tripled in 2013 and has grown to be one of the largest communities of women engineers in the world.

Empowerment:

Women Who code is a professional community for women in tech. We provide an avenue for women to pursue a career in technology, help them gain new skills and hone existing skills for professional advancement, and foster environments where networking and mentorship are valued.

Key Initiatives:

Free technical study groups

Events featuring influential tech industry experts and investors

Hack events

Career and leadership development

Current and aspiring coders are welcome. 

Bring your laptop and a friend! 

Support Women Who Code:

Donating to Women Who Code, Inc. (#46-4218859) directly impacts our ability to efficiently run this growing organization, helps us produce new programs that will increase our reach, and enables us to expand into new cities around the world ensuring that women and girls everywhere have the opportunity to pursue a career in technology.

Women Who Code (WWCode) is dedicated to providing an empowering experience for everyone who participates in or supports our community, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, ability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or socioeconomic status. Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. Our Code of Conduct applies to all events run by Women Who Code, Inc. If you would like to report an incident or contact our leadership team, please submit an incident report form.

WomenWhoCode.com

Twitter | Facebook
description.421: We love polyglots, people who care about craftsmanship and best practices. Come join us and let's learn to use tools that are fit for their purpose; let's scrutinize the worthiness of new technologies; let's practice what we preach and let's hangout together.
description.422: The Philadelphia Network Programmability User's Group (NPUG) is a monthly meetup to learn about the latest technology around SDN and network programmability. The world of networking is evolving quickly - software defined networking, API's, Python, open source, automation, and other technologies are being introduced and it's clear there's a new skill set required with the next wave of technology. The Network Programmability User's Group is a community built around learning and sharing to help people in different roles get started with the new technology trends - like programming networks.
description.423: Get ready to talk Python / Djanjo! We're looking to engage professionals living in or around North Jersey to form a community closer to home.  We love and use Python / Django! If you do too and and are interested in discussions regarding the language please join us at our next meeting to  share the knowledge and build a community.
description.424:
Free office hours for programming help. This is a group for anyone who needs help with learning to code or making progress on a project, and for those who are willing to help others to become better developers.

The "Hacker Hours" concept was pioneered in NYC by Aidan Feldman: hackerhours.org
description.425: This is a group for anyone interested in functional programming, whether it's pure functional languages like Haskell, impure functional languages like Clojure, or languages like Python and Ruby which have the capabilities. All levels of experience and interest are welcome, and hopefully we can foster passion for functional programming in Grand Rapids.
description.426:
BOSS is a non-profit organization of individuals interested in learning and developing Open source software in the Birmingham, AL area. We are made up of Ruby, Python, Javascript, Arduino and other OSS programmers. BOSS welcomes anyone who feels they would fit in, or would like to, as our primary goal is to strengthen the Open Source development community in the Birmingham Area.

Meetings are held the last Monday of every month, barring holiday conflicts.

 

IRC: #bhamboss on FreeNode
description.427: This is a group for anyone interested in coding Python from beginning to expert level. I started this group because I wanted foster a place in Gainesville where other Python devs could meet up, converse and code. Topics that we'll work on include Django web development, Kivy mobile applications, and general Python programs.
description.428: This meetup group is for anyone in Iowa who wants to sync up, meet new people, learn cool stuff, and generally geek out in a very relaxed and informal setting.  We discuss a very broad range of Information Security topics, and mainly use this group to stay in touch and get the word out about related events in Iowa. If you or someone you know likes to hack, crack, code, build, break, fuzz, prevent, detect, or respond to things for fun or profit... you'll be in good company here. Please join our group and stop on out to one of our next meet-ups, we'd love to have you.
description.429: This is a meetup for systems administrators, data center operators, DevOps-minded folks, SaltStack customers, users and contributors. SaltStack is software used for enterprise scale infrastructure automation, cloud orchestration and application deployment and configuration management. The Salt open source software project was written in Python and according to GitHub is one of the largest and most active open source projects in the world. SaltStack is used by Web-scale IT organizations like LinkedIn, Hulu, Salesforce.com, NASA JPL, Clemson University, Photobucket, XMission, and thousands more.
description.430: San Antonio Pyladies for anyone interested in learning more about Python. This is a mentoring group for women, men who encourage and support women in technology are welcome to join for mentoring and to be mentored. We will have talks all Python related as well as workshops and social hours. We are just getting off the ground, so bare with us as we make it through this year.
description.431: Developers and enthusiast interested in promoting diversity and education in the Python development community.
description.432:
This is a group for people interested in high quality code... doesn't really matter what language, what methodology, or what kind of environment you work in (big enterprise, startup, open source, etc.). All that matters is that you're interested in getting together now and then (in real life or virtually) to talk about great code and what makes it great.

BTW, I know there's a "thing" around software craftsmanship (not to mention a conference coming to LA in 2015) and we should talk about that movement. But the time we spend together in these Meetups should be much broader, focused only on high quality code and not centered around any manifestos.

Long term, the goal is to give members the tools (and inspire them) to write amazing code accomplish by learning from others, study, mentorship, hands on experience, and open discussion.
description.433: We are a Python meetup group in Sunnyvale. There is no membership fee and all are welcome. Only you need to bring your interest in learning and teaching Python and all its amazing packages and modules.
description.434: This is a group for everyone who is interested in networking technologies and in particular those people keen to learn about areas such as Software Defined Networks (SDN) network automation and cloud. We will be meeting to talk about innovation on the network and in particular innovations in Data Centre technology. Those people using or interested in using Arista technology in their networks are welcome but that isn't a requirement to attend!
description.435:
EPIK (Encouraging Programming In Kids) is a voluntary Kent based Mozilla youth group for geeky youths and their families. EPIK’s focus is to encourage programming, this both within a technical context and also as developing social skills through peer to peer collaborative projects which we wrap in Arts Award.

in 2015 we are focusing on our teens to get them to experience and meet the industry by hosting events at technical conferences where they get to meet the experts, ask questions and in some cases offered summer volunteering and internship opportunities to help them make an informed choice pre degree or apprenticeship path.
description.436:
Membres d'Okiwi, nous sommes une communautée de développeurs passionnés qui échangent sur les pratiques avancées d'ingénieurie logicielle. Ainsi, quel que soit ton langage ou framework de prédilection soit le bienvenu parmi nous. 

Afin de conserver l'esprit de ce groupe, nous sommes attachés aux valeurs suivantes : 

• Le savoir à long terme : nous développons des connaissances indépendantes de la technologie utilisée en se concentrant sur les fondamentaux de l’ingénieurie logicielle (plutôt que sur les derniers outils à la mode). 

• Bien faire les choses : nous cherchons la meilleure façon de résoudre un problème et mettons de la fierté dans notre travail (et non notre égo). 

• Bienveillants envers le reste de la communauté : nous sommes tous là pour apprendre et partager notre savoir (c'est pourquoi nous évitons les trolls stériles).
description.437:
coding and talking about volunteer-planner.org (and sister projects). 

Fork us on GitHub: https://github.com/volunteer-planner/volunteer_planner
description.438: Seja bem vindo ao grupy-rp! O grupo de usuários Python de Ribeirão Preto. O grupy-rp é composto por apaixonados pela linguagem Python. São muito bem vindos pessoas de outras tecnologias, de qualquer nível de conhecimento, desde a pessoa iniciante até o mais experiente.
description.439: Newtown Partners and Silicon Cape are hosting startup matchmaking events in Cape Town and Johannesburg - startupmatch.co.za. Prior to the events, we'll be selecting 15 high potential startups looking for either a technical co-founder or software engineers to join their team. We’re looking for 100 of Cape Town's brightest software developers that are interested in getting involved in a startup, to join us on the day. We'll then arrange "speed dates" between the shortlisted startups and the 100 or so software engineers looking for a new challenge. There are no costs to attend. We also have an awesome lineup of keynote talks. We think that this kind of startup match-making event is missing from the local startup ecosystem. Too many South African startups don't have technical co-founders and this needs to change. We hope that we'll be able to host these startup match-making events more regularly in Cape Town and Johannesburg and that the matchups will play an important part in creating more successful startups in South Africa.
description.440:
This is a group for professional developers and users of the Python programming language in New Zealand to expand our network of people, opportunities and ideas.

We have monthly meetings with presentations - if you're interested, please join the group and check out our website for further information.

This meetup.com group is for Christchurch meetings.
description.441:
A group for Python enthusiasts to share ideas and learn from each other about how best to apply our language and tools to ever-evolving challenges in the vast realm of data management, processing, analytics, and visualization.

Github: https://github.com/pydatasg
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydatasg

All things web technology from web design to software engineering to systems administration. All interest and skill levels welcome.

Panhandle Web Tech meets on the third Tuesday of each month @Firebrand Media located in downtown Martinsburg, WV.

218 West King St
Martinsburg, WV 25401

• people interested in learning to code

We'll get together and share ideas. If you have anything in particular you'd like to present for a meetup, let me know!

description.445: We are a Tech Center when the Norcross Community can get together and discuss coding, web development, start up, community development, Opportunity Hub, and other creative ideas.
description.446: Whether you're a certified Pythonista or just curious about getting started with the Python programming language, join us on the third Monday of each month at The Factory in Grand Rapids, Michigan for our regular meetings. Every member is both a teacher and a student committed to making themselves and their peers better programmers. We welcome everyone at Hacker Base Camp; there are absolutely no restrictions on level of experience.
description.448: This is a group for anyone interested in learning technology skills. We embrace all modern technologies and offer workshops and classes to anyone who wants to learn how to code using the latest technologies. Front end development, back end development and full-stack engineering.
description.449: This group is a place for developers, systems admins, and tech enthusiasts to learn more about the open source, document-oriented database MongoDB.  MongoDB is the leading NoSQL database and many organizations are adopting this technology.  If you are facing challenges with MySQL or Postgres or Oracle and want to explore a more flexible, scalable alternative, please join us at one of our sessions.
description.450: We are Django users, programmers, and overall enthusiasts. description.455:
La intención es la de fortalecer a la comunidad de desarrolladores y entusiastas de Python  en las inmediaciones de la Ciudad de México.

Python es un lenguaje de programación que tiene muchas vertientes y posibilidades, pero que necesita de una comunidad más activa y organizada.

Las reuniones en vivo de pythonistas son un buen pretexto para conocernos y compartir conocimientos y experiencias en aras de hacer una gran comunidad.
description.456:
Boise Area Python Users Group (BAPUG) meets monthly to share new ideas and learn more about the Python programming language. We enlist the help of intermediate and advanced users to share how they use the language, along with tips and tricks for others. 

We welcome beginners, and our goal is to be helpful and nurturing to all. We are an open community, and we do not discriminate against anyone, for any reason, nor do we tolerate those that do.

We hope to grow BAPUG into a vibrant community, with strong local participation. We want BAPUG to be the best place to learn and share about Python and Python related topics.

Since the founding members of the group also have web development experience and interests, BAPUG will also include talks about web frameworks, including Django, Flask, Pylons, etc. Python is a rich language, and is used a many areas, so we hope to have talk covering NLP, Computer vision, Game programming, 3D Animation, numerical programming, and any other areas where Python is used.
description.457:
Local user group for Django and related technologies.

Find us in IRC on Freenode: #django-seattle
description.458:
Google Developer Group Trondheim, aka "GDG Trondheim", is a non-profit developer group to learn, share and know more about Google technologies.

 

We have a G+ community site here: http://goo.gl/JzQrh. We'll try to share photos, useful links and other interesting information there.

 

Also, we're present on Twitter: https://twitter.com/GDGTrondheim
description.459:
Am 28.11 findet in Köln zum ersten Mal ein Django Girls Event statt: Einstieg ins Programmieren für Frauen und Mädchen ab 18 Jahre ohne Vorkenntnisse in einer NETTEN Atmosphäre - darauf legen wir Wert. Django Girls sind kostenfrei, weltweit von Freiwilligen organisiert und von Sponsoren finanziert. Anmeldung bis 07.11. Wir haben nur ca. 30 Plätze, also schnell anmelden.
Wer Coach sein möchte oder uns unterstützen will, ist auch herzlich willkommen.
(Extra Termin für Männer/Jungs auf Anfrage. )
http://djangogirls.org/cologne/
Die Meetup-Gruppe ist dafür gedacht, nach dem Django Girls Event Kontakt zu halten und weitere Treffen zu organisieren, in denen die Frauen und Mädchen Erfahrungen austauschen, gemeinsam weiter lernen und auch erste Projekte umsetzen können. Zudem hoffe ich, dass wir so eine Community gründen, um weitere Django Girls Events in Köln zu veranstalten.
description.460:
Este es el grupo de Codecademy de la región de Murcia. Las meetups de codecademy son para aprender sobre los cursos de Codecademy (que son gratuitos) y para aprender a programar; a ser un Coder. En este grupo vas a hacer amigos con otros que están aprendiendo como tú, para soporte mutuo en durante el aprendizaje. Cualquiera que sea tu nivel actual, novato y hacker; y sin importar si eres estudiante o profesional; ni edad, ni raza, ni género, ni religión. Solo ganas de aprender a programar en un entorno de iguales. Te deseamos la bienvenida a nuestro grupo, y esperamos verte en nuestras reuniones. A qué esperas? Aprendamos a programar, juntos.

This is the Codecademy meetup in Murcia, Spain. Codecademy Meetups are a place where you can come to learn more about Codecademy courses and programming languages, make friends with fellow learners, and help one another as you go through your coding journey. You can be a student or a professional, any age, race, gender, or religion. We welcome everyone to come together and learn to code in a supportive environment full of your peers. Want to get into programming? What are you waiting for? Let's code together.
description.461: Groupe d'utilisateurs de Python pour discuter de tout ce qui tourne autour de Python mais aussi d'autres langages et technologies developeurs.
description.462:
Wir treffen uns jeden zweiten Mittwoch im Monat im Meetingraum des Grünhofs um uns über die verschiedenen Anwendungen von Python auszutauschen.

Die Teilnahme am Meetup ist kostenlos, allerdings haben wir Kosten zu tragen (36€ Raummiete/pro Treffen, 12$ Meetup.com Gebühr/Quartal). Wer es sich leisten kann ist daher eingeladen sich mit 5€ pro Treffen an den Kosten zu beteiligen.
description.463: Web Monday ist ein informelles, nicht-kommerzielles, dezentral organisiertes Treffen, das zum Ziel hat, all diejenigen miteinander zu verbinden, die die Zukunft des Internets gestalten.
description.464: For everone in Budapest who love to work with Django. Interesting discussions, job openings, start-up news and much more. - Join this meetup to discuss all things django!
description.465:
You like automating the heck out of infrastructure? Play with Docker, Ansible, Nagios or Chef much? We're a group of complete nerds who enjoy monitoring, configuration management, continuous integration and pentest. Some of us even grow beards and like to make Linux jokes.

We're meeting every month for a couple presentations and some good ol' geeking out. Join us!
description.466:
這是一群由新手及具經驗的開發者組成的團體，我們 hack 任何與 DNS 有關的事物。我們專注於與 DNS 相關的主題，例如新的域名後綴上線、使用域名建立 mail 及架站、如何將域名及DNS與其他服務結合。

A group of beginner and advanced developers who hack anything related to DNS. We focus on DNS related topics (new extensions, how to setup mail/web services with your domain), as well as building websites and how to combine those with other services.
description.467:
Welcome to PyHUG!  We are a group of Python programmers near the Hsinchu, Taiwan.  We regularly hold seminar and coding meetings.  You are very welcomed to join us!  You can also find us online at Freenode/#python.tw IRC room and https://groups.google.com/d/forum/pythontw Google group.

 

歡迎來到 PyHUG。我們是一群活動於新竹周邊的 Python 程式員。我們會定期舉辦技術討論與程式設計的聚會。非常歡迎你加入我們！你也可以在 Freenode/#python.tw IRC room 和 https://groups.google.com/d/forum/pythontw Google group 裡找到我們。
description.468:
The topics at jnaapti's meetups range from discussions about Map/Reduce design patterns, discussions on programming paradigms to the future of Client Side Technologies. With just 13 meetups till date, we have built a community of 700+ members from over 50 companies, members who are serious about technological developments. jnaapti's meetups have been hosted by companies like Akamai and NASSCOM Startup Warehouse. The reviews we have received and the comments that people have posted for our past meetups are a testimony to the quality of the sessions we deliver.

jnaapti is a technical skill development company providing customized and personalized learning solutions to the masses. In the last 4 years we have trained hundreds of professionals in over 25 companies on more than 30 different free software technologies. We also train engineering students through a workshop called the Fast Trackers Workshop and help them by providing a platform to build and nurture their engineering skill-set. Our intention is to make computer science education fun and involving. We specialize in providing coaching in niche areas in web engineering like AngularJS, Docker, Cloud Computing, Hadoop, NodeJS, etc. We are also building a revolutionary learning product called the "Virtual Coach".

The whole philosophy behind the jnaapti approach is that people should be self-reliant when it comes to learning. Learners are taught "how to learn" keeping in mind the fact that, in this world where technologies change rapidly, change is the only constant and what is relevant now may not exist soon and re-training is expensive.

Learners work on a learning path that is customized after assessing their current skills and the skills they intend to pickup.

Find more here jnaapti.com
description.469: BrisbanePUG A monthly get-together of the Python Users in Brisbane to discuss problems, share interesting developments and provide an audience for presentations. Food and drink are provided by our sponsor Netbox Blue. We use the brispy google group as a mailing list.
description.470: Computer programmers, Web developers of queens unite. No more long commutes to the city to get and give help on your stalled projects. Why not create our own group here in queens where we can meet-up*, learn from each other, help each other and have a fun time doing it. This group is for anyone interested in software development/computer programming, specifically for those living in the queens area who like me have had to go to meet-ups in the city and are looking to stay closer to home.
description.471:
Rochester's Python Users Group

RocPy is Rochester's local (and only!) Python user group. We exist to give others the opportunity to work and play with local Python developers, learners, employers, and enthusiasts. All skill levels are welcome, if you are interested in Python, join us!

  • Monthly presentation series: these are 45-60 minutes presentations on topics of interest to the Python community.
  • We also plan on having 5-10 minute lightning talks as well. Soon, we'll have a signup process for members wishing to participate!
  • Monthly weekend workshops are also planned.
description.472:
Total immersion in all things open source: Java, Python, Android, Linux, Hadoop, NoSQL, Web, Mobile, LAMP, VoIP, and many other open source related topics.

Monthly meetings to network with fellow developers passionate about open source technology.

Guest speakers and panels, networking, giveaways/prizes...and in the true nature of open source, this meetup group is what YOU make it!

Here's a link to our GitHub:

https://github.com/fwin-dev
description.473:
Welcome to Chadev Python
The Chattanooga developer python user group

Socialize with us at our monthly meeting where we have presentations on all things python. This is a great opportunity to converse with other like minded python enthusiasts to talk about projects, problems and techniques. Our meetup is composed of local python developers, employers, enthusiasts, hobbyists, students and programmers of many languages. This is a place of learning so we welcome all levels of knowledge. As a sub-group of Chadev we abide by Chadev's Code of Conduct
description.474:
Google Developers' Group St Louis aim is to bring together experts, beginners and enthusiasts alike to meet and discuss a wide array of topics related to Google technologies and writing code that uses Google Cloud, Android, Chrome, Google product APIs. Our meetings are always free and open to the general public. We will sometimes co-host joint meetings with other St Louis MeetUp groups.

Disclaimer: GDG St Louis is an independent group; our activities and the opinions expressed here should in no way be linked to Google, the corporation.
description.475:
So who is a Hacker?

In a nutshell, they are anyone who solves a problem with a not-so-obvious solution with only the resources available to them. MacGyver was the quintessential hacker! We think everyone has a little MacGyver in them. If you've created some improvised pressure cooker, or maybe turned your computer into a central home management system, Hack and Tell is a group where you can share your ideas with other clever members.

Hack and Tell?

We're a group of technophiles! We organize engaging events to share discussion on all things programming, robotics, advances in tech research and current events. We originally started putting on regular events for hackers to show off fun projects they've been working on. We had excellent projects shared and are still looking for more. We also regularly get together to talk about the latest technology trends and events....over beer (and sometimes BRUNCH!) Not to mention other community events we like to participate in as a group.

Sounds great! Now what?

Then RSVP to our next event!! If you're thinking about presenting something but haven't finalized your plans, feel free to email the organizer, Mike (that's me), and I'll help answer any questions you have. This doesn't commit you to anything! We will email you to get details or help get your presentation from brainmatter to paper if you need it.

Hack and Tell is in other cities, too!

Visit http://hackandtell.org for more info.
description.476:

Join us on IRC: #flinthillsio on Freenode

Website: http://flinthills.io
description.477: A meetup for systems administrators, DevOps-minded folks, SaltStack customers, users and contributors.
